var book = {
	"name": "2 Samuel",
	"numChapters": 24,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>Now it came about after <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8024A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8024A\"></sup>the death of Saul, when David had returned from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8024B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8024B\"></sup>the slaughter of the Amalekites, that David remained two days in Ziklag.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>On the third day, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8025C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8025C\"></sup>a man came out of the camp from Saul, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8025D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8025D\"></sup>with his clothes torn and dust on his head. And it came about when he came to David that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8025E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8025E\"></sup>he fell to the ground and prostrated himself.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then David said to him, “From where do you come?” And he said to him, “I have escaped from the camp of Israel.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8027F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8027F\"></sup>How did things go? Please tell me.” And he said, “The people have fled from the battle, and also many of the people have fallen and are dead; and Saul and Jonathan his son are dead also.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So David said to the young man who told him, “How do you know that Saul and his son Jonathan are dead?”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>The young man who told him said, “By chance I happened to be on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8029G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8029G\"></sup>Mount Gilboa, and behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8029H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8029H\"></sup>Saul was leaning on his spear. And behold, the chariots and the horsemen pursued him closely.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When he looked behind him, he saw me and called to me. And I said, ‘Here I am.’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>He said to me, ‘Who are you?’ And I answered him, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8031I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8031I\"></sup>I am an Amalekite.’",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he said to me, ‘Please stand beside me and kill me, for agony has seized me because my life still lingers in me.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So I stood beside him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8033J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8033J\"></sup>and killed him, because I knew that he could not live after he had fallen. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8033K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8033K\"></sup>I took the crown which <i>was</i> on his head and the bracelet which <i>was</i> on his arm, and I have brought them here to my lord.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8034L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8034L\"></sup>David took hold of his clothes and tore them, and <i>so</i> also <i>did</i> all the men who <i>were</i> with him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>They mourned and wept and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8035M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8035M\"></sup>fasted until evening for Saul and his son Jonathan and for the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and the house of Israel, because they had fallen by the sword.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>David said to the young man who told him, “Where are you from?” And he answered, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8036N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8036N\"></sup>I am the son of an alien, an Amalekite.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then David said to him, “How is it you were not afraid <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8037O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8037O\"></sup>to stretch out your hand to destroy the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed?”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And David called one of the young men and said, “Go, cut him down.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8038P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8038P\"></sup>So he struck him and he died.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8039Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8039Q\"></sup>Your blood is on your head, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8039R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8039R\"></sup>your mouth has testified against you, saying, ‘I have killed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8040S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8040S\"></sup>chanted with this lament over Saul and Jonathan his son,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>and he told <i>them</i> to teach the sons of Judah <i>the song of</i> the bow; behold, it is written in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8041T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8041T\"></sup>the book of Jashar.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“Your beauty, O Israel, is slain on your high places!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8042U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8042U\"></sup>How have the mighty fallen!",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8043V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8043V\"></sup>Tell <i>it</i> not in Gath,Proclaim it not in the streets of Ashkelon,Or <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8043W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8043W\"></sup>the daughters of the Philistines will rejoice,The daughters of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8043X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8043X\"></sup>the uncircumcised will exult.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8044Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8044Y\"></sup>O mountains of Gilboa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8044Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8044Z\"></sup>Let not dew or rain be on you, nor fields of offerings;For there the shield of the mighty was defiled,The shield of Saul, not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8044AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8044AA\"></sup>anointed with oil.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8045AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8045AB\"></sup>From the blood of the slain, from the fat of the mighty,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8045AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8045AC\"></sup>The bow of Jonathan did not turn back,And the sword of Saul did not return empty.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“Saul and Jonathan, beloved and pleasant in their life,And in their death they were not parted;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8046AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8046AD\"></sup>They were swifter than eagles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8046AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8046AE\"></sup>They were stronger than lions.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“O daughters of Israel, weep over Saul,Who clothed you luxuriously in scarlet,Who put ornaments of gold on your apparel.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8048AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8048AF\"></sup>How have the mighty fallen in the midst of the battle!Jonathan is slain on your high places.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“I am distressed for you, my brother Jonathan;You have been very pleasant to me.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8049AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8049AG\"></sup>Your love to me was more wonderfulThan the love of women.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8050AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8050AH\"></sup>How have the mighty fallen,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8050AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8050AI\"></sup>the weapons of war perished!”"
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Then it came about afterwards that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8051A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8051A\"></sup>David inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “Shall I go up to one of the cities of Judah?” And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to him, “Go up.” So David said, “Where shall I go up?” And He said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8051B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8051B\"></sup>To Hebron.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So David went up there, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8052C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8052C\"></sup>his two wives also, Ahinoam the Jezreelitess and Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8053D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8053D\"></sup>David brought up his men who <i>were</i> with him, each with his household; and they lived in the cities of Hebron.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the men of Judah came and there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8054E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8054E\"></sup>anointed David king over the house of Judah.And they told David, saying, “It was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8054F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8054F\"></sup>the men of Jabesh-gilead who buried Saul.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>David sent messengers to the men of Jabesh-gilead, and said to them, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8055G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8055G\"></sup>May you be blessed of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> because you have shown this kindness to Saul your lord, and have buried him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8056H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8056H\"></sup>may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> show lovingkindness and truth to you; and I also will show this goodness to you, because you have done this thing.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now therefore, let your hands be strong and be valiant; for Saul your lord is dead, and also the house of Judah has anointed me king over them.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8058I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8058I\"></sup>Abner the son of Ner, commander of Saul’s army, had taken Ish-bosheth the son of Saul and brought him over to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8058J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8058J\"></sup>Mahanaim.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He made him king over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8059K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8059K\"></sup>Gilead, over the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8059L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8059L\"></sup>Ashurites, over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8059M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8059M\"></sup>Jezreel, over Ephraim, and over Benjamin, even over all Israel.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Ish-bosheth, Saul’s son, was forty years old when he became king over Israel, and he was king for two years. The house of Judah, however, followed David.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8061N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8061N\"></sup>The time that David was king in Hebron over the house of Judah was seven years and six months.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now Abner the son of Ner, went out from Mahanaim to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8062O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8062O\"></sup>Gibeon with the servants of Ish-bosheth the son of Saul.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8063P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8063P\"></sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah and the servants of David went out and met them by the pool of Gibeon; and they sat down, one on the one side of the pool and the other on the other side of the pool.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Abner said to Joab, “Now let the young men arise and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8064Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8064Q\"></sup>hold a contest before us.” And Joab said, “Let them arise.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So they arose and went over by count, twelve for Benjamin and Ish-bosheth the son of Saul, and twelve of the servants of David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Each one of them seized his opponent by the head and <i>thrust</i> his sword in his opponent’s side; so they fell down together. Therefore that place was called Helkath-hazzurim, which is in Gibeon.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>That day the battle was very severe, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8067R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8067R\"></sup>Abner and the men of Israel were beaten before the servants of David.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8068S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8068S\"></sup>the three sons of Zeruiah were there, Joab and Abishai and Asahel; and Asahel <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8068T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8068T\"></sup><i>as</i> swift-footed as one of the gazelles which is in the field.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Asahel pursued Abner and did not turn to the right or to the left from following Abner.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Abner looked behind him and said, “Is that you, Asahel?” And he answered, “It is I.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So Abner said to him, “Turn to your right or to your left, and take hold of one of the young men for yourself, and take for yourself his spoil.” But Asahel was not willing to turn aside from following him.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Abner repeated again to Asahel, “Turn aside from following me. Why should I strike you to the ground? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8072U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8072U\"></sup>How then could I lift up my face to your brother Joab?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>However, he refused to turn aside; therefore Abner struck him in the belly with the butt end of the spear, so that the spear came out at his back. And he fell there and died on the spot. And it came about that all who came to the place where <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8073V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8073V\"></sup>Asahel had fallen and died, stood still.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>But Joab and Abishai pursued Abner, and when the sun was going down, they came to the hill of Ammah, which is in front of Giah by the way of the wilderness of Gibeon.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The sons of Benjamin gathered together behind Abner and became one band, and they stood on the top of a certain hill.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then Abner called to Joab and said, “Shall the sword devour forever? Do you not know that it will be bitter in the end? How long will you refrain from telling the people to turn back from following their brothers?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Joab said, “As God lives, if you had not spoken, surely then the people would have gone away in the morning, each from following his brother.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>So Joab blew the trumpet; and all the people halted and pursued Israel no longer, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8078W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8078W\"></sup>nor did they continue to fight anymore.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Abner and his men then went through the Arabah all that night; so they crossed the Jordan, walked all morning, and came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8079X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8079X\"></sup>Mahanaim.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then Joab returned from following Abner; when he had gathered all the people together, nineteen of David’s servants besides Asahel were missing.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>But the servants of David had struck down many of Benjamin and Abner’s men, <i>so that</i> three hundred and sixty men died.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And they took up Asahel and buried him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8082Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8082Y\"></sup>in his father’s tomb which was in Bethlehem. Then Joab and his men went all night until the day dawned at Hebron."
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8083A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8083A\"></sup>there was a long war between the house of Saul and the house of David; and David grew steadily stronger, but the house of Saul grew weaker continually.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8084B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8084B\"></sup>Sons were born to David at Hebron: his firstborn was Amnon, by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8084C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8084C\"></sup>Ahinoam the Jezreelitess;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and his second, Chileab, by Abigail the widow of Nabal the Carmelite; and the third, Absalom the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8085D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8085D\"></sup>Maacah, the daughter of Talmai, king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8085E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8085E\"></sup>Geshur;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>and the fourth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8086F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8086F\"></sup>Adonijah the son of Haggith; and the fifth, Shephatiah the son of Abital;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and the sixth, Ithream, by David’s wife Eglah. These were born to David at Hebron.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>It came about while there was war between the house of Saul and the house of David that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8088G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8088G\"></sup>Abner was making himself strong in the house of Saul.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now Saul had a concubine whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8089H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8089H\"></sup>Rizpah, the daughter of Aiah; and Ish-bosheth said to Abner, “Why have you gone in to my father’s concubine?”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then Abner was very angry over the words of Ish-bosheth and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8090I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8090I\"></sup>Am I a dog’s head that belongs to Judah? Today I show kindness to the house of Saul your father, to his brothers and to his friends, and have not delivered you into the hands of David; and yet today you charge me with a guilt concerning the woman.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8091J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8091J\"></sup>May God do so to Abner, and more also, if <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8091K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8091K\"></sup>as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has sworn to David, I do not accomplish this for him,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8092L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8092L\"></sup>to transfer the kingdom from the house of Saul and to establish the throne of David over Israel and over Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8092M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8092M\"></sup>from Dan even to Beersheba.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And he could no longer answer Abner a word, because he was afraid of him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then Abner sent messengers to David in his place, saying, “Whose is the land? Make your covenant with me, and behold, my hand shall be with you to bring all Israel over to you.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He said, “Good! I will make a covenant with you, but I demand one thing of you, namely, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8095N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8095N\"></sup>you shall not see my face unless you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8095O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8095O\"></sup>first bring Michal, Saul’s daughter, when you come to see me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So David sent messengers to Ish-bosheth, Saul’s son, saying, “Give me my wife Michal, to whom I was betrothed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8096P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8096P\"></sup>for a hundred foreskins of the Philistines.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ish-bosheth sent and took her from <i>her</i> husband, from Paltiel the son of Laish.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But her husband went with her, weeping as he went, and followed her as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8098Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8098Q\"></sup>Bahurim. Then Abner said to him, “Go, return.” So he returned.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now Abner had consultation with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8099R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8099R\"></sup>the elders of Israel, saying, “In times past you were seeking for David to be king over you.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now then, do <i>it</i>! For the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has spoken of David, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8100S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8100S\"></sup>By the hand of My servant David I will save My people Israel from the hand of the Philistines and from the hand of all their enemies.’”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Abner also spoke in the hearing of Benjamin; and in addition Abner went to speak in the hearing of David in Hebron all that seemed good to Israel and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8101T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8101T\"></sup>the whole house of Benjamin.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Abner and twenty men with him came to David at Hebron. And David made a feast for Abner and the men who were with him.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Abner said to David, “Let me arise and go and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8103U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8103U\"></sup>gather all Israel to my lord the king, that they may make a covenant with you, and that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8103V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8103V\"></sup>you may be king over all that your soul desires.” So David sent Abner away, and he went in peace.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>And behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8104W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8104W\"></sup>the servants of David and Joab came from a raid and brought much spoil with them; but Abner was not with David in Hebron, for he had sent him away, and he had gone in peace.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When Joab and all the army that was with him arrived, they told Joab, saying, “Abner the son of Ner came to the king, and he has sent him away, and he has gone in peace.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then Joab came to the king and said, “What have you done? Behold, Abner came to you; why then have you sent him away and he is already gone?",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>You know Abner the son of Ner, that he came to deceive you and to learn of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8107X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8107X\"></sup>your going out and coming in and to find out all that you are doing.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When Joab came out from David, he sent messengers after Abner, and they brought him back from the well of Sirah; but David did not know <i>it</i>.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>So when Abner returned to Hebron, Joab took him aside into the middle of the gate to speak with him privately, and there <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8109Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8109Y\"></sup>he struck him in the belly so that he died on account of the blood of Asahel his brother.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Afterward when David heard it, he said, “I and my kingdom are innocent before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> forever of the blood of Abner the son of Ner.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8111Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8111Z\"></sup>May it fall on the head of Joab and on all his father’s house; and may there not fail from the house of Joab <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8111AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8111AA\"></sup>one who has a discharge, or who is a leper, or who takes hold of a distaff, or who falls by the sword, or who lacks bread.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>So Joab and Abishai his brother killed Abner <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8112AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8112AB\"></sup>because he had put their brother Asahel to death in the battle at Gibeon.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then David said to Joab and to all the people who were with him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8113AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8113AC\"></sup>Tear your clothes and gird on sackcloth and lament before Abner.” And King David walked behind the bier.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Thus they buried Abner in Hebron; and the king lifted up his voice and wept at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8114AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8114AD\"></sup>the grave of Abner, and all the people wept.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8115AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8115AE\"></sup>The king chanted a <i>lament</i> for Abner and said,“Should Abner die as a fool dies?",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“Your hands were not bound, nor your feet put in fetters;As one falls before the wicked, you have fallen.”And all the people wept again over him.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then all the people came <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8117AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8117AF\"></sup>to persuade David to eat bread while it was still day; but David vowed, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8117AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8117AG\"></sup>May God do so to me, and more also, if I taste bread or anything else <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8117AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8117AH\"></sup>before the sun goes down.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Now all the people took note <i>of it</i>, and it pleased them, just as everything the king did pleased all the people.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So all the people and all Israel understood that day that it had not been <i>the will</i> of the king to put Abner the son of Ner to death.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Then the king said to his servants, “Do you not know that a prince and a great man has fallen this day in Israel?",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>I am <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8121AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8121AI\"></sup>weak today, though anointed king; and these men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8121AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8121AJ\"></sup>the sons of Zeruiah are too difficult for me. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8121AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8121AK\"></sup>May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> repay the evildoer according to his evil.”"
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>Now when Ish-bosheth, Saul’s son, heard that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8122A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8122A\"></sup>Abner had died in Hebron, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8122B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8122B\"></sup>he lost courage, and all Israel was disturbed.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Saul’s son <i>had</i> two men who were commanders of bands: the name of the one was Baanah and the name of the other Rechab, sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, of the sons of Benjamin (for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8123C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8123C\"></sup>Beeroth is also considered <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8123D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8123D\"></sup><i>part</i> of Benjamin,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and the Beerothites fled to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8124E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8124E\"></sup>Gittaim and have been aliens there until this day).",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8125F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8125F\"></sup>Jonathan, Saul’s son, had a son crippled in his feet. He was five years old when the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8125G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8125G\"></sup>report of Saul and Jonathan came from Jezreel, and his nurse took him up and fled. And it happened that in her hurry to flee, he fell and became lame. And his name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8125H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8125H\"></sup>Mephibosheth.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So the sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, Rechab and Baanah, departed and came to the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8126I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8126I\"></sup>Ish-bosheth in the heat of the day while he was taking his midday rest.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>They came to the middle of the house as if to get wheat, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8127J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8127J\"></sup>they struck him in the belly; and Rechab and Baanah his brother escaped.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now when they came into the house, as he was lying on his bed in his bedroom, they struck him and killed him and beheaded him. And they took his head and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8128K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8128K\"></sup>traveled by way of the Arabah all night.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then they brought the head of Ish-bosheth to David at Hebron and said to the king, “Behold, the head of Ish-bosheth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8129L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8129L\"></sup>the son of Saul, your enemy, who sought your life; thus the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given my lord the king vengeance this day on Saul and his descendants.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>David answered Rechab and Baanah his brother, sons of Rimmon the Beerothite, and said to them, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8130M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8130M\"></sup>who has redeemed my life from all distress,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8131N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8131N\"></sup>when one told me, saying, ‘Behold, Saul is dead,’ and thought he was bringing good news, I seized him and killed him in Ziklag, which was the reward I gave him for <i>his</i> news.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>How much more, when wicked men have killed a righteous man in his own house on his bed, shall I not now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8132O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8132O\"></sup>require his blood from your hand and destroy you from the earth?”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8133P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8133P\"></sup>David commanded the young men, and they killed them and cut off their hands and feet and hung them up beside the pool in Hebron. But they took the head of Ish-bosheth <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8133Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8133Q\"></sup>and buried it in the grave of Abner in Hebron."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8134A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8134A\"></sup>Then all the tribes of Israel came to David at Hebron and said, “Behold, we are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8134B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8134B\"></sup>your bone and your flesh.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Previously, when Saul was king over us, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8135C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8135C\"></sup>you were the one who led Israel out and in. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to you, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8135D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8135D\"></sup>You will shepherd My people Israel, and you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8135E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8135E\"></sup>a ruler over Israel.’”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So all the elders of Israel came to the king at Hebron, and King David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8136F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8136F\"></sup>made a covenant with them before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> at Hebron; then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8136G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8136G\"></sup>they anointed David king over Israel.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8137H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8137H\"></sup>thirty years old when he became king, <i>and</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8137I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8137I\"></sup>he reigned forty years.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>At Hebron <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8138J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8138J\"></sup>he reigned over Judah seven years and six months, and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty-three years over all Israel and Judah.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8139K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8139K\"></sup>Now the king and his men went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8139L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8139L\"></sup>Jerusalem against the Jebusites, the inhabitants of the land, and they said to David, “You shall not come in here, but the blind and lame will turn you away”; thinking, “David cannot enter here.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nevertheless, David captured the stronghold of Zion, that is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8140M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8140M\"></sup>the city of David.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>David said on that day, “Whoever would strike the Jebusites, let him reach the lame and the blind, who are hated by David’s soul, through the water tunnel.” Therefore they say, “The blind or the lame shall not come into the house.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So David lived in the stronghold and called it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8142N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8142N\"></sup>the city of David. And David built all around from the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8142O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8142O\"></sup>Millo and inward.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8143P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8143P\"></sup>David became greater and greater, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of hosts was with him.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8144Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8144Q\"></sup>Then Hiram king of Tyre sent messengers to David with cedar trees and carpenters and stonemasons; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8144R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8144R\"></sup>they built a house for David.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And David realized that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had established him as king over Israel, and that He had exalted his kingdom for the sake of His people Israel.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Meanwhile <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8146S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8146S\"></sup>David took more concubines and wives from Jerusalem, after he came from Hebron; and more sons and daughters were born to David.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8147T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8147T\"></sup>these are the names of those who were born to him in Jerusalem: Shammua, Shobab, Nathan, Solomon,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Ibhar, Elishua, Nepheg, Japhia,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Elishama, Eliada and Eliphelet.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>When the Philistines heard that they had anointed David king over Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8150U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8150U\"></sup>all the Philistines went up to seek out David; and when David heard <i>of it</i>, he went down to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8150V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8150V\"></sup>stronghold.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now the Philistines came and spread themselves out in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8151W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8151W\"></sup>the valley of Rephaim.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8152X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8152X\"></sup>David inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, saying, “Shall I go up against the Philistines? Will You give them into my hand?” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8152Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8152Y\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said to David, “Go up, for I will certainly give the Philistines into your hand.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So David came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8153Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8153Z\"></sup>Baal-perazim and defeated them there; and he said, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has broken through my enemies before me like the breakthrough of waters.” Therefore he named that place Baal-perazim.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>They abandoned their idols there, so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8154AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8154AA\"></sup>David and his men carried them away.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8155AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8155AB\"></sup>the Philistines came up once again and spread themselves out in the valley of Rephaim.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8156AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8156AC\"></sup>David inquired of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, He said, “You shall not go <i>directly</i> up; circle around behind them and come at them in front of the balsam trees.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>It shall be, when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8157AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8157AD\"></sup>you hear the sound of marching in the tops of the balsam trees, then you shall act promptly, for then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8157AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8157AE\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will have gone out before you to strike the army of the Philistines.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then David did so, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded him, and struck down the Philistines from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8158AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8158AF\"></sup>Geba as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8158AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8158AG\"></sup>Gezer."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8159A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8159A\"></sup>Now David again gathered all the chosen men of Israel, thirty thousand.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And David arose and went with all the people who were with him to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8160B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8160B\"></sup>Baale-judah, to bring up from there the ark of God which is called by the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8160C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8160C\"></sup>Name, the very name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8160D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8160D\"></sup>is enthroned <i>above</i> the cherubim.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>They placed the ark of God on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8161E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8161E\"></sup>a new cart that they might bring it from the house of Abinadab which was on the hill; and Uzzah and Ahio, the sons of Abinadab, were leading the new cart.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8162F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8162F\"></sup>they brought it with the ark of God from the house of Abinadab, which was on the hill; and Ahio was walking ahead of the ark.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Meanwhile, David and all the house of Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8163G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8163G\"></sup>were celebrating before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8163H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8163H\"></sup>with all kinds of <i>instruments made of</i> fir wood, and with lyres, harps, tambourines, castanets and cymbals.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>But when they came to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8164I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8164I\"></sup>threshing floor of Nacon, Uzzah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8164J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8164J\"></sup>reached out toward the ark of God and took hold of it, for the oxen nearly upset <i>it</i>.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against Uzzah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8165K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8165K\"></sup>God struck him down there for his irreverence; and he died there by the ark of God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>David became angry because of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> outburst against Uzzah, and that place is called Perez-uzzah to this day.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8167L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8167L\"></sup>David was afraid of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> that day; and he said, “How can the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> come to me?”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And David was unwilling to move the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> into the city of David with him; but David took it aside to the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8168M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8168M\"></sup>Obed-edom the Gittite.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> remained in the house of Obed-edom the Gittite three months, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8169N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8169N\"></sup>blessed Obed-edom and all his household.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Now it was told King David, saying, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has blessed the house of Obed-edom and all that belongs to him, on account of the ark of God.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8170O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8170O\"></sup>David went and brought up the ark of God from the house of Obed-edom into <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8170P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8170P\"></sup>the city of David with gladness.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And so it was, that when the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8171Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8171Q\"></sup>bearers of the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had gone six paces, he sacrificed an <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8171R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8171R\"></sup>ox and a fatling.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8172S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8172S\"></sup>David was dancing before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with all <i>his</i> might, and David was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8172T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8172T\"></sup>wearing a linen ephod.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So David and all the house of Israel were bringing up the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with shouting and the sound of the trumpet.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then it happened <i>as</i> the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came into the city of David that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8174U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8174U\"></sup>Michal the daughter of Saul looked out of the window and saw King David leaping and dancing before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>; and she despised him in her heart.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So they brought in the ark of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and set it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8175V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8175V\"></sup>in its place inside the tent which David had pitched for it; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8175W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8175W\"></sup>David offered burnt offerings and peace offerings before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>When David had finished offering the burnt offering and the peace offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8176X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8176X\"></sup>he blessed the people in the name of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Further, he distributed to all the people, to all the multitude of Israel, both to men and women, a cake of bread and one of dates and one of raisins to each one. Then all the people departed each to his house.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But when David returned to bless his household, Michal the daughter of Saul came out to meet David and said, “How the king of Israel distinguished himself today! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8178Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8178Y\"></sup>He uncovered himself today in the eyes of his servants’ maids as one of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8178Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8178Z\"></sup>foolish ones shamelessly uncovers himself!”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So David said to Michal, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8179AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8179AA\"></sup><i>It was</i> before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, who chose me above your father and above all his house, to appoint me ruler over the people of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, over Israel; therefore I will celebrate before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I will be more lightly esteemed than this and will be humble in my own eyes, but with the maids of whom you have spoken, with them I will be distinguished.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Michal the daughter of Saul had no child to the day of her death."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8182A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8182A\"></sup>Now it came about when the king lived in his house, and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had given him rest on every side from all his enemies,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that the king said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8183B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8183B\"></sup>Nathan the prophet, “See now, I dwell in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8183C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8183C\"></sup>a house of cedar, but the ark of God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8183D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8183D\"></sup>dwells within tent curtains.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Nathan said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8184E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8184E\"></sup>Go, do all that is in your mind, for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is with you.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>But in the same night the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to Nathan, saying,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Go and say to My servant David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8186F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8186F\"></sup>Are you the one who should build Me a house to dwell in?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8187G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8187G\"></sup>I have not dwelt in a house since the day I brought up the sons of Israel from Egypt, even to this day; but I have been moving about <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8187H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8187H\"></sup>in a tent, even in a tabernacle.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8188I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8188I\"></sup>Wherever I have gone with all the sons of Israel, did I speak a word with one of the tribes of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8188J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8188J\"></sup>which I commanded to shepherd My people Israel, saying, ‘Why have you not built Me a house of cedar?’”’",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Now therefore, thus you shall say to My servant David, ‘Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8189K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8189K\"></sup>I took you from the pasture, from following the sheep, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8189L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8189L\"></sup>to be ruler over My people Israel.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8190M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8190M\"></sup>I have been with you wherever you have gone and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8190N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8190N\"></sup>have cut off all your enemies from before you; and I will make you a great name, like the names of the great men who are on the earth.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I will also appoint a place for My people Israel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8191O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8191O\"></sup>will plant them, that they may live in their own place and not be disturbed again, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8191P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8191P\"></sup>nor will the wicked afflict them any more as formerly,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8192Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8192Q\"></sup>from the day that I commanded judges to be over My people Israel; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8192R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8192R\"></sup>I will give you rest from all your enemies. The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also declares to you that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8192S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8192S\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will make a house for you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8193T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8193T\"></sup>When your days are complete and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8193U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8193U\"></sup>lie down with your fathers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8193V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8193V\"></sup>I will raise up your descendant after you, who will come forth from you, and I will establish his kingdom.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8194W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8194W\"></sup>He shall build a house for My name, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8194X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8194X\"></sup>I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8195Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8195Y\"></sup>I will be a father to him and he will be a son to Me; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8195Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8195Z\"></sup>when he commits iniquity, I will correct him with the rod of men and the strokes of the sons of men,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>but My lovingkindness shall not depart from him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8196AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8196AA\"></sup>as I took <i>it</i> away from Saul, whom I removed from before you.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8197AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8197AB\"></sup>Your house and your kingdom shall endure before Me forever; your throne shall be established forever.”’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>In accordance with all these words and all this vision, so Nathan spoke to David.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then David the king went in and sat before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8199AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8199AC\"></sup>Who am I, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, and what is my house, that You have brought me this far?",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And yet this was insignificant in Your eyes, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8200AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8200AD\"></sup>for You have spoken also of the house of Your servant concerning the distant future. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8200AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8200AE\"></sup>this is the custom of man, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Again what more can David say to You? For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8201AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8201AF\"></sup>You know Your servant, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8202AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8202AG\"></sup>For the sake of Your word, and according to Your own heart, You have done all this greatness to let Your servant know.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For this reason <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8203AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8203AH\"></sup>You are great, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8203AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8203AI\"></sup>there is none like You, and there is no God besides You, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8203AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8203AJ\"></sup>according to all that we have heard with our ears.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8204AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8204AK\"></sup>what one nation on the earth is like Your people Israel, whom God went to redeem for Himself as a people and to make a name for Himself, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8204AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8204AL\"></sup>to do a great thing for You and awesome things for Your land, before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8204AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8204AM\"></sup>Your people whom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8204AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8204AN\"></sup>You have redeemed for Yourself from Egypt, <i>from</i> nations and their gods?",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8205AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8205AO\"></sup>You have established for Yourself Your people Israel as Your own people forever, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8205AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8205AP\"></sup>You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, have become their God.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now therefore, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God, the word that You have spoken concerning Your servant and his house, confirm <i>it</i> forever, and do as You have spoken,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8207AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8207AQ\"></sup>that Your name may be magnified forever, by saying, ‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts is God over Israel’; and may the house of Your servant David be established before You.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>For You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> of hosts, the God of Israel, have made a revelation to Your servant, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8208AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8208AR\"></sup>I will build you a house’; therefore Your servant has found courage to pray this prayer to You.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, You are God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8209AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8209AS\"></sup>Your words are truth, and You have promised this good thing to Your servant.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Now therefore, may it please You to bless the house of Your servant, that it may continue forever before You. For You, O Lord <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">God</span>, have spoken; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8210AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8210AT\"></sup>with Your blessing may the house of Your servant be blessed forever.”"
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8211A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8211A\"></sup>Now after this it came about that David defeated the Philistines and subdued them; and David took control of the chief city from the hand of the Philistines.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8212B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8212B\"></sup>He defeated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8212C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8212C\"></sup>Moab, and measured them with the line, making them lie down on the ground; and he measured two lines to put to death and one full line to keep alive. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8212D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8212D\"></sup>the Moabites became servants to David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8212E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8212E\"></sup>bringing tribute.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then David defeated <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8213F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8213F\"></sup>Hadadezer, the son of Rehob king of Zobah, as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8213G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8213G\"></sup>he went to restore his rule at the River.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David captured from him 1,700 horsemen and 20,000 foot soldiers; and David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8214H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8214H\"></sup>hamstrung the chariot horses, but reserved <i>enough</i> of them for 100 chariots.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8215I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8215I\"></sup>the Arameans of Damascus came to help Hadadezer, king of Zobah, David killed 22,000 Arameans.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then David put garrisons among the Arameans of Damascus, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8216J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8216J\"></sup>the Arameans became servants to David, bringing tribute. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8216K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8216K\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helped David wherever he went.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David took the shields of gold which were carried by the servants of Hadadezer and brought them to Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>From Betah and from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8218L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8218L\"></sup>Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, King David took a very large amount of bronze.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now when Toi king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8219M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8219M\"></sup>Hamath heard that David had defeated all the army of Hadadezer,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Toi sent Joram his son to King David to greet him and bless him, because he had fought against Hadadezer and defeated him; for Hadadezer had been at war with Toi. And <i>Joram</i> brought with him articles of silver, of gold and of bronze.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>King David also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8221N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8221N\"></sup>dedicated these to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, with the silver and gold that he had dedicated from all the nations which he had subdued:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>from Aram and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8222O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8222O\"></sup>Moab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8222P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8222P\"></sup>the sons of Ammon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8222Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8222Q\"></sup>the Philistines and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8222R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8222R\"></sup>Amalek, and from the spoil of Hadadezer, son of Rehob, king of Zobah.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8223S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8223S\"></sup>David made a name <i>for himself</i> when he returned from killing 18,000 Arameans in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8223T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8223T\"></sup>the Valley of Salt.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He put garrisons in Edom. In all Edom he put garrisons, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8224U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8224U\"></sup>all the Edomites became servants to David. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8224V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8224V\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> helped David wherever he went.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So David reigned over all Israel; and David administered justice and righteousness for all his people.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8226W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8226W\"></sup>Joab the son of Zeruiah <i>was</i> over the army, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8226X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8226X\"></sup>Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8226Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8226Y\"></sup>recorder.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8227Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8227Z\"></sup>Zadok the son of Ahitub and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar <i>were</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8227AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8227AA\"></sup>priests, and Seraiah <i>was</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8227AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8227AB\"></sup>secretary.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8228AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8228AC\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8228AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8228AD\"></sup>Cherethites and the Pelethites; and David’s sons were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8228AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8228AE\"></sup>chief ministers."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Then David said, “Is there yet anyone left of the house of Saul, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8229A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8229A\"></sup>that I may show him kindness for Jonathan’s sake?”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now there was a servant of the house of Saul whose name was Ziba, and they called him to David; and the king said to him, “Are you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8230B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8230B\"></sup>Ziba?” And he said, “<i>I am</i> your servant.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The king said, “Is there not yet anyone of the house of Saul to whom I may show the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8231C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8231C\"></sup>kindness of God?” And Ziba said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8231D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8231D\"></sup>There is still a son of Jonathan who is crippled in both feet.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the king said to him, “Where is he?” And Ziba said to the king, “Behold, he is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8232E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8232E\"></sup>in the house of Machir the son of Ammiel in Lo-debar.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then King David sent and brought him from the house of Machir the son of Ammiel, from Lo-debar.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8234F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8234F\"></sup>Mephibosheth, the son of Jonathan the son of Saul, came to David and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8234G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8234G\"></sup>fell on his face and prostrated himself. And David said, “Mephibosheth.” And he said, “Here is your servant!”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>David said to him, “Do not fear, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8235H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8235H\"></sup>I will surely show kindness to you for the sake of your father Jonathan, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8235I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8235I\"></sup>will restore to you all the land of your grandfather Saul; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8235J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8235J\"></sup>you shall eat at my table regularly.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Again he prostrated himself and said, “What is your servant, that you should regard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8236K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8236K\"></sup>a dead dog like me?”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then the king called Saul’s servant Ziba and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8237L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8237L\"></sup>All that belonged to Saul and to all his house I have given to your master’s grandson.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>You and your sons and your servants shall cultivate the land for him, and you shall bring in <i>the produce</i> so that your master’s grandson may have food; nevertheless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8238M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8238M\"></sup>Mephibosheth your master’s grandson <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8238N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8238N\"></sup>shall eat at my table regularly.” Now Ziba had fifteen sons and twenty servants.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Ziba said to the king, “According <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8239O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8239O\"></sup>to all that my lord the king commands his servant so your servant will do.” So Mephibosheth ate at David’s table as one of the king’s sons.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Mephibosheth had a young son whose name was Mica. And all who lived in the house of Ziba were servants to Mephibosheth.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Mephibosheth lived in Jerusalem, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8241P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8241P\"></sup>he ate at the king’s table regularly. Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8241Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8241Q\"></sup>he was lame in both feet."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8242A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8242A\"></sup>Now it happened afterwards that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8242B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8242B\"></sup>the king of the Ammonites died, and Hanun his son became king in his place.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then David said, “I will show kindness to Hanun the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8243C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8243C\"></sup>Nahash, just as his father showed kindness to me.” So David sent some of his servants to console him concerning his father. But when David’s servants came to the land of the Ammonites,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the princes of the Ammonites said to Hanun their lord, “Do you think that David is honoring your father because he has sent consolers to you? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8244D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8244D\"></sup>Has David not sent his servants to you in order to search the city, to spy it out and overthrow it?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So Hanun took David’s servants and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8245E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8245E\"></sup>shaved off half of their beards, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8245F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8245F\"></sup>cut off their garments in the middle as far as their hips, and sent them away.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When they told <i>it</i> to David, he sent to meet them, for the men were greatly humiliated. And the king said, “Stay at Jericho until your beards grow, and <i>then</i> return.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now when the sons of Ammon saw that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8247G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8247G\"></sup>they had become odious to David, the sons of Ammon sent and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8247H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8247H\"></sup>hired the Arameans of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8247I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8247I\"></sup>Beth-rehob and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8247J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8247J\"></sup>Arameans of Zobah, 20,000 foot soldiers, and the king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8247K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8247K\"></sup>Maacah with 1,000 men, and the men of Tob with 12,000 men.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When David heard <i>of it</i>, he sent Joab and all the army, the mighty men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The sons of Ammon came out and drew up in battle array <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8249L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8249L\"></sup>at the entrance of the city, while the Arameans of Zobah and of Rehob and the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8249M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8249M\"></sup>Tob and Maacah <i>were</i> by themselves in the field.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now when Joab saw that the battle was set against him in front and in the rear, he selected from all the choice men of Israel, and arrayed <i>them</i> against the Arameans.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the remainder of the people he placed in the hand of Abishai his brother, and he arrayed <i>them</i> against the sons of Ammon.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>He said, “If the Arameans are too strong for me, then you shall help me, but if the sons of Ammon are too strong for you, then I will come to help you.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8253N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8253N\"></sup>Be strong, and let us show ourselves courageous for the sake of our people and for the cities of our God; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8253O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8253O\"></sup>may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> do what is good in His sight.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Joab and the people who were with him drew near to the battle against the Arameans, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8254P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8254P\"></sup>they fled before him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>When the sons of Ammon saw that the Arameans fled, they <i>also</i> fled before Abishai and entered the city. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8255Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8255Q\"></sup>Then Joab returned from <i>fighting</i> against the sons of Ammon and came to Jerusalem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When the Arameans saw that they had been defeated by Israel, they gathered themselves together.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8257R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8257R\"></sup>And Hadadezer sent and brought out the Arameans who were beyond the River, and they came to Helam; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8257S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8257S\"></sup>Shobach the commander of the army of Hadadezer led them.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now when it was told David, he gathered all Israel together and crossed the Jordan, and came to Helam. And the Arameans arrayed themselves to meet David and fought against him.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But the Arameans fled before Israel, and David killed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8259T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8259T\"></sup>700 charioteers of the Arameans and 40,000 horsemen and struck down Shobach the commander of their army, and he died there.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>When all the kings, servants of Hadadezer, saw that they were defeated by Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8260U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8260U\"></sup>they made peace with Israel and served them. So the Arameans feared to help the sons of Ammon anymore."
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8261A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8261A\"></sup>Then it happened <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8261B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8261B\"></sup>in the spring, at the time when kings go out <i>to battle</i>, that David sent Joab and his servants with him and all Israel, and they destroyed the sons of Ammon and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8261C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8261C\"></sup>besieged Rabbah. But David stayed at Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Now when evening came David arose from his bed and walked around on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8262D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8262D\"></sup>the roof of the king’s house, and from the roof he saw a woman bathing; and the woman was very beautiful in appearance.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So David sent and inquired about the woman. And one said, “Is this not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8263E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8263E\"></sup>Bathsheba, the daughter of Eliam, the wife of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8263F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8263F\"></sup>Uriah the Hittite?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>David sent messengers and took her, and when she came to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8264G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8264G\"></sup>he lay with her; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8264H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8264H\"></sup>and when she had purified herself from her uncleanness, she returned to her house.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The woman conceived; and she sent and told David, and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8265I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8265I\"></sup>I am pregnant.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then David sent to Joab, <i>saying</i>, “Send me Uriah the Hittite.” So Joab sent Uriah to David.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>When Uriah came to him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8267J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8267J\"></sup>David asked concerning the welfare of Joab and the people and the state of the war.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then David said to Uriah, “Go down to your house, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8268K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8268K\"></sup>wash your feet.” And Uriah went out of the king’s house, and a present from the king was sent out after him.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>But Uriah slept <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8269L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8269L\"></sup>at the door of the king’s house with all the servants of his lord, and did not go down to his house.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now when they told David, saying, “Uriah did not go down to his house,” David said to Uriah, “Have you not come from a journey? Why did you not go down to your house?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Uriah said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8271M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8271M\"></sup>The ark and Israel and Judah are staying in temporary shelters, and my lord Joab and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8271N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8271N\"></sup>the servants of my lord are camping in the open field. Shall I then go to my house to eat and to drink and to lie with my wife? By your life and the life of your soul, I will not do this thing.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then David said to Uriah, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8272O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8272O\"></sup>Stay here today also, and tomorrow I will let you go.” So Uriah remained in Jerusalem that day and the next.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now David called him, and he ate and drank before him, and he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8273P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8273P\"></sup>made him drunk; and in the evening he went out to lie on his bed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8273Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8273Q\"></sup>with his lord’s servants, but he did not go down to his house.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now in the morning David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8274R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8274R\"></sup>wrote a letter to Joab and sent <i>it</i> by the hand of Uriah.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8275S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8275S\"></sup>He had written in the letter, saying, “Place Uriah in the front line of the fiercest battle and withdraw from him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8275T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8275T\"></sup>so that he may be struck down and die.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So it was as Joab kept watch on the city, that he put Uriah at the place where he knew there <i>were</i> valiant men.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The men of the city went out and fought against Joab, and some of the people among David’s servants fell; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8277U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8277U\"></sup>Uriah the Hittite also died.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Joab sent and reported to David all the events of the war.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He charged the messenger, saying, “When you have finished telling all the events of the war to the king,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>and if it happens that the king’s wrath rises and he says to you, ‘Why did you go so near to the city to fight? Did you not know that they would shoot from the wall?",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8281V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8281V\"></sup>struck down Abimelech the son of Jerubbesheth? Did not a woman throw an upper millstone on him from the wall so that he died at Thebez? Why did you go so near the wall?’—then you shall say, ‘Your servant Uriah the Hittite is dead also.’”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So the messenger departed and came and reported to David all that Joab had sent him <i>to tell</i>.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The messenger said to David, “The men prevailed against us and came out against us in the field, but we pressed them as far as the entrance of the gate.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Moreover, the archers shot at your servants from the wall; so some of the king’s servants are dead, and your servant Uriah the Hittite is also dead.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Then David said to the messenger, “Thus you shall say to Joab, ‘Do not let this thing displease you, for the sword devours one as well as another; make your battle against the city stronger and overthrow it’; and <i>so</i> encourage him.”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Now when the wife of Uriah heard that Uriah her husband was dead, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8286W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8286W\"></sup>she mourned for her husband.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>When the <i>time of</i> mourning was over, David sent and brought her to his house and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8287X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8287X\"></sup>she became his wife; then she bore him a son. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8287Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8287Y\"></sup>the thing that David had done was evil in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8288A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8288A\"></sup>Nathan to David. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8288B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8288B\"></sup>he came to him and said,“There were two men in one city, the one rich and the other poor.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“The rich man had a great many flocks and herds.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“But the poor man had nothing except <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8290C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8290C\"></sup>one little ewe lambWhich he bought and nourished;And it grew up together with him and his children.It would eat of his bread and drink of his cup and lie in his bosom,And was like a daughter to him.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“Now a traveler came to the rich man,And he was unwilling to take from his own flock or his own herd,To prepare for the wayfarer who had come to him;Rather he took the poor man’s ewe lamb and prepared it for the man who had come to him.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then David’s anger burned greatly against the man, and he said to Nathan, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, surely the man who has done this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8292D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8292D\"></sup>deserves to die.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He must make restitution for the lamb <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8293E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8293E\"></sup>fourfold, because he did this thing and had no compassion.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Nathan then said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8294F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8294F\"></sup>You are the man! Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of Israel, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8294G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8294G\"></sup>It is I who anointed you king over Israel and it is I who delivered you from the hand of Saul.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>I also gave you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8295H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8295H\"></sup>your master’s house and your master’s wives into your care, and I gave you the house of Israel and Judah; and if <i>that had been</i> too little, I would have added to you many more things like these!",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Why <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8296I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8296I\"></sup>have you despised the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> by doing evil in His sight? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8296J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8296J\"></sup>You have struck down Uriah the Hittite with the sword, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8296K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8296K\"></sup>have taken his wife to be your wife, and have killed him with the sword of the sons of Ammon.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now therefore, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8297L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8297L\"></sup>the sword shall never depart from your house, because you have despised Me and have taken the wife of Uriah the Hittite to be your wife.’",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Thus says the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, ‘Behold, I will raise up evil against you from your own household; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8298M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8298M\"></sup>I will even take your wives before your eyes and give <i>them</i> to your companion, and he will lie with your wives in broad daylight.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Indeed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8299N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8299N\"></sup>you did it secretly, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8299O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8299O\"></sup>I will do this thing before all Israel, and under the sun.’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then David said to Nathan, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8300P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8300P\"></sup>I have sinned against the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And Nathan said to David, “The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> also has <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8300Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8300Q\"></sup>taken away your sin; you shall not die.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>However, because by this deed you have <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8301R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8301R\"></sup>given occasion to the enemies of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> to blaspheme, the child also that is born to you shall surely die.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So Nathan went to his house.Then the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> struck the child that Uriah’s widow bore to David, so that he was <i>very</i> sick.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>David therefore inquired of God for the child; and David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8303S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8303S\"></sup>fasted and went and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8303T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8303T\"></sup>lay all night on the ground.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8304U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8304U\"></sup>The elders of his household stood beside him in order to raise him up from the ground, but he was unwilling and would not eat food with them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then it happened on the seventh day that the child died. And the servants of David were afraid to tell him that the child was dead, for they said, “Behold, while the child was <i>still</i> alive, we spoke to him and he did not listen to our voice. How then can we tell him that the child is dead, since he might do <i>himself</i> harm!”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when David saw that his servants were whispering together, David perceived that the child was dead; so David said to his servants, “Is the child dead?” And they said, “He is dead.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>So David arose from the ground, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8307V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8307V\"></sup>washed, anointed <i>himself</i>, and changed his clothes; and he came into the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8307W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8307W\"></sup>worshiped. Then he came to his own house, and when he requested, they set food before him and he ate.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then his servants said to him, “What is this thing that you have done? While the child was alive, you fasted and wept; but when the child died, you arose and ate food.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>He said, “While the child was <i>still</i> alive, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8309X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8309X\"></sup>I fasted and wept; for I said, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8309Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8309Y\"></sup>Who knows, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> may be gracious to me, that the child may live.’",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>But now he has died; why should I fast? Can I bring him back again? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8310Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8310Z\"></sup>I will go to him, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8310AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8310AA\"></sup>he will not return to me.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then David comforted his wife Bathsheba, and went in to her and lay with her; and she gave birth to a son, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8311AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8311AB\"></sup>he named him Solomon. Now the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> loved him",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and sent <i>word</i> through Nathan the prophet, and he named him Jedidiah for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> sake.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8313AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8313AC\"></sup>Now Joab fought against <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8313AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8313AD\"></sup>Rabbah of the sons of Ammon and captured the royal city.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Joab sent messengers to David and said, “I have fought against Rabbah, I have even captured the city of waters.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now therefore, gather the rest of the people together and camp against the city and capture it, or I will capture the city myself and it will be named after me.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So David gathered all the people and went to Rabbah, fought against it and captured it.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8317AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8317AE\"></sup>he took the crown of their king from his head; and its weight <i>was</i> a talent of gold, and <i>in it</i> <i>was</i> a precious stone; and it was <i>placed</i> on David’s head. And he brought out the spoil of the city in great amounts.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>He also brought out the people who were in it, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8318AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8318AF\"></sup>set <i>them</i> under saws, sharp iron instruments, and iron axes, and made them pass through the brickkiln. And thus he did to all the cities of the sons of Ammon. Then David and all the people returned <i>to</i> Jerusalem."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>Now it was after this that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8319A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8319A\"></sup>Absalom the son of David had a beautiful sister whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8319B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8319B\"></sup>Tamar, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8319C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8319C\"></sup>Amnon the son of David loved her.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Amnon was so frustrated because of his sister Tamar that he made himself ill, for she was a virgin, and it seemed hard to Amnon to do anything to her.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Amnon had a friend whose name was Jonadab, the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8321D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8321D\"></sup>Shimeah, David’s brother; and Jonadab was a very shrewd man.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>He said to him, “O son of the king, why are you so depressed morning after morning? Will you not tell me?” Then Amnon said to him, “I am in love with Tamar, the sister of my brother Absalom.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Jonadab then said to him, “Lie down on your bed and pretend to be ill; when your father comes to see you, say to him, ‘Please let my sister Tamar come and give me <i>some</i> food to eat, and let her prepare the food in my sight, that I may see <i>it</i> and eat from her hand.’”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So Amnon lay down and pretended to be ill; when the king came to see him, Amnon said to the king, “Please let my sister Tamar come and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8324E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8324E\"></sup>make me a couple of cakes in my sight, that I may eat from her hand.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then David sent to the house for Tamar, saying, “Go now to your brother Amnon’s house, and prepare food for him.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So Tamar went to her brother Amnon’s house, and he was lying down. And she took dough, kneaded <i>it</i>, made cakes in his sight, and baked the cakes.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>She took the pan and dished <i>them</i> out before him, but he refused to eat. And Amnon said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8327F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8327F\"></sup>Have everyone go out from me.” So everyone went out from him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Amnon said to Tamar, “Bring the food into the bedroom, that I may eat from your hand.” So Tamar took the cakes which she had made and brought them into the bedroom to her brother Amnon.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When she brought <i>them</i> to him to eat, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8329G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8329G\"></sup>took hold of her and said to her, “Come, lie with me, my sister.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But she answered him, “No, my brother, do not violate me, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8330H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8330H\"></sup>such a thing is not done in Israel; do not do this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8330I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8330I\"></sup>disgraceful thing!",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As for me, where could I get rid of my reproach? And as for you, you will be like one of the fools in Israel. Now therefore, please speak to the king, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8331J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8331J\"></sup>he will not withhold me from you.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>However, he would not listen to her; since he was stronger than she, he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8332K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8332K\"></sup>violated her and lay with her.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then Amnon hated her with a very great hatred; for the hatred with which he hated her was greater than the love with which he had loved her. And Amnon said to her, “Get up, go away!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>But she said to him, “No, because this wrong in sending me away is greater than the other that you have done to me!” Yet he would not listen to her.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then he called his young man who attended him and said, “Now throw this woman out of my <i>presence</i>, and lock the door behind her.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now she had on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8336L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8336L\"></sup>a long-sleeved garment; for in this manner the virgin daughters of the king dressed themselves in robes. Then his attendant took her out and locked the door behind her.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8337M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8337M\"></sup>Tamar put ashes on her head and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8337N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8337N\"></sup>tore her long-sleeved garment which <i>was</i> on her; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8337O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8337O\"></sup>she put her hand on her head and went away, crying aloud as she went.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Absalom her brother said to her, “Has Amnon your brother been with you? But now keep silent, my sister, he is your brother; do not take this matter to heart.” So Tamar remained and was desolate in her brother Absalom’s house.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now when King David heard of all these matters, he was very angry.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>But Absalom did not speak to Amnon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8340P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8340P\"></sup>either good or bad; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8340Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8340Q\"></sup>Absalom hated Amnon because he had violated his sister Tamar.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now it came about after two full years that Absalom <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8341R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8341R\"></sup>had sheepshearers in Baal-hazor, which is near Ephraim, and Absalom invited all the king’s sons.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Absalom came to the king and said, “Behold now, your servant has sheepshearers; please let the king and his servants go with your servant.”",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>But the king said to Absalom, “No, my son, we should not all go, for we will be burdensome to you.” Although he urged him, he would not go, but blessed him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8344S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8344S\"></sup>Absalom said, “If not, please let my brother Amnon go with us.” And the king said to him, “Why should he go with you?”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>But when Absalom urged him, he let Amnon and all the king’s sons go with him.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Absalom commanded his servants, saying, “See now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8346T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8346T\"></sup>when Amnon’s heart is merry with wine, and when I say to you, ‘Strike Amnon,’ then put him to death. Do not fear; have not I myself commanded you? Be courageous and be valiant.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The servants of Absalom did to Amnon just as Absalom had commanded. Then all the king’s sons arose and each mounted <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8347U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8347U\"></sup>his mule and fled.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Now it was while they were on the way that the report came to David, saying, “Absalom has struck down all the king’s sons, and not one of them is left.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then the king arose, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8349V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8349V\"></sup>tore his clothes and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8349W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8349W\"></sup>lay on the ground; and all his servants were standing by with clothes torn.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8350X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8350X\"></sup>Jonadab, the son of Shimeah, David’s brother, responded, “Do not let my lord suppose they have put to death all the young men, the king’s sons, for Amnon alone is dead; because by the intent of Absalom this has been determined since the day that he violated his sister Tamar.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Now therefore, do not let my lord the king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8351Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8351Y\"></sup>take the report to heart, namely, ‘all the king’s sons are dead,’ for only Amnon is dead.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8352Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8352Z\"></sup>Absalom had fled. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8352AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8352AA\"></sup>the young man who was the watchman raised his eyes and looked, and behold, many people were coming from the road behind him by the side of the mountain.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Jonadab said to the king, “Behold, the king’s sons have come; according to your servant’s word, so it happened.”",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>As soon as he had finished speaking, behold, the king’s sons came and lifted their voices and wept; and also the king and all his servants wept very bitterly.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8355AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8355AB\"></sup>Absalom fled and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8355AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8355AC\"></sup>Talmai the son of Ammihud, the king of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8355AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8355AD\"></sup>Geshur. And <i>David</i> mourned for his son every day.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8356AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8356AE\"></sup>So Absalom had fled and gone to Geshur, and was there three years.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><i>The heart of</i> King David longed to go out to Absalom; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8357AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8357AF\"></sup>he was comforted concerning Amnon, since he was dead."
		},
		"14": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">14 </span>Now Joab the son of Zeruiah perceived that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8358A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8358A\"></sup>the king’s heart <i>was inclined</i> toward Absalom.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Joab sent to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8359B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8359B\"></sup>Tekoa and brought a wise woman from there and said to her, “Please pretend to be a mourner, and put on mourning garments now, and do not <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8359C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8359C\"></sup>anoint yourself with oil, but be like a woman who has been mourning for the dead many days;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>then go to the king and speak to him in this manner.” So Joab put <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8360D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8360D\"></sup>the words in her mouth.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now when the woman of Tekoa spoke to the king, she fell on her face to the ground and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8361E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8361E\"></sup>prostrated herself and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8361F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8361F\"></sup>Help, O king.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king said to her, “What is your trouble?” And she answered, “Truly I am a widow, for my husband is dead.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Your maidservant had two sons, but the two of them struggled together in the field, and there was no one to separate them, so one struck the other and killed him.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8364G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8364G\"></sup>the whole family has risen against your maidservant, and they say, ‘Hand over the one who struck his brother, that we may put him to death for the life of his brother whom he killed, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8364H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8364H\"></sup>and destroy the heir also.’ Thus they will extinguish my coal which is left, so as to leave my husband neither name nor remnant on the face of the earth.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then the king said to the woman, “Go to your house, and I will give orders concerning you.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The woman of Tekoa said to the king, “O my lord, the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8366I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8366I\"></sup>the iniquity is on me and my father’s house, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8366J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8366J\"></sup>the king and his throne are guiltless.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>So the king said, “Whoever speaks to you, bring him to me, and he will not touch you anymore.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then she said, “Please let the king remember the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8368K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8368K\"></sup><i>so that</i> the avenger of blood will not continue to destroy, otherwise they will destroy my son.” And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8368L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8368L\"></sup>As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, not one hair of your son shall fall to the ground.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then the woman said, “Please let your maidservant speak a word to my lord the king.” And he said, “Speak.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The woman said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8370M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8370M\"></sup>Why then have you planned such a thing against the people of God? For in speaking this word the king is as one who is guilty, <i>in that</i> the king does not bring back <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8370N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8370N\"></sup>his banished one.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8371O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8371O\"></sup>we will surely die and are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8371P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8371P\"></sup>like water spilled on the ground which cannot be gathered up again. Yet God does not take away life, but plans ways so that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8371Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8371Q\"></sup>the banished one will not be cast out from him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now the reason I have come to speak this word to my lord the king is that the people have made me afraid; so your maidservant said, ‘Let me now speak to the king, perhaps the king will perform the request of his maidservant.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>For the king will hear and deliver his maidservant from the hand of the man who would destroy both me and my son from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8373R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8373R\"></sup>the inheritance of God.’",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then your maidservant said, ‘Please let the word of my lord the king be comforting, for as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8374S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8374S\"></sup>the angel of God, so is my lord the king to discern good and evil. And may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God be with you.’”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then the king answered and said to the woman, “Please do not hide anything from me that I am about to ask you.” And the woman said, “Let my lord the king please speak.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So the king said, “Is the hand of Joab with you in all this?” And the woman replied, “As your soul lives, my lord the king, no one can turn to the right or to the left from anything that my lord the king has spoken. Indeed, it was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8376T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8376T\"></sup>your servant Joab who commanded me, and it was he who put all these words in the mouth of your maidservant;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>in order to change the appearance of things your servant Joab has done this thing. But my lord is wise, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8377U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8377U\"></sup>like the wisdom of the angel of God, to know all that is in the earth.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then the king said to Joab, “Behold now, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8378V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8378V\"></sup>I will surely do this thing; go therefore, bring back the young man Absalom.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Joab fell on his face to the ground, prostrated himself and blessed the king; then Joab said, “Today your servant knows that I have found favor in your sight, O my lord, the king, in that the king has performed the request of his servant.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So Joab arose and went to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8380W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8380W\"></sup>Geshur and brought Absalom to Jerusalem.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>However the king said, “Let him turn to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8381X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8381X\"></sup>his own house, and let him not see my face.” So Absalom turned to his own house and did not see the king’s face.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Now in all Israel was no one as handsome as Absalom, so highly praised; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8382Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8382Y\"></sup>from the sole of his foot to the crown of his head there was no defect in him.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>When he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8383Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8383Z\"></sup>cut the hair of his head (and it was at the end of every year that he cut <i>it</i>, for it was heavy on him so he cut it), he weighed the hair of his head at 200 shekels by the king’s weight.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8384AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8384AA\"></sup>To Absalom there were born three sons, and one daughter whose name was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8384AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8384AB\"></sup>Tamar; she was a woman of beautiful appearance.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Now Absalom lived two full years in Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8385AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8385AC\"></sup>and did not see the king’s face.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Then Absalom sent for Joab, to send him to the king, but he would not come to him. So he sent again a second time, but he would not come.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Therefore he said to his servants, “See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8387AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8387AD\"></sup>Joab’s field is next to mine, and he has barley there; go and set it on fire.” So Absalom’s servants set the field on fire.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then Joab arose, came to Absalom at his house and said to him, “Why have your servants set my field on fire?”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Absalom answered Joab, “Behold, I sent for you, saying, ‘Come here, that I may send you to the king, to say, “Why have I come from Geshur? It would be better for me still to be there.”’ Now therefore, let me see the king’s face, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8389AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8389AE\"></sup>and if there is iniquity in me, let him put me to death.”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>So when Joab came to the king and told him, he called for Absalom. Thus he came to the king and prostrated himself on his face to the ground before the king, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8390AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8390AF\"></sup>the king kissed Absalom."
		},
		"15": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">15 </span>Now it came about after this that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8391A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8391A\"></sup>Absalom provided for himself a chariot and horses and fifty men as runners before him.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Absalom used to rise early and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8392B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8392B\"></sup>stand beside the way to the gate; and when any man had a suit to come to the king for judgment, Absalom would call to him and say, “From what city are you?” And he would say, “Your servant is from one of the tribes of Israel.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then Absalom would say to him, “See, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8393C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8393C\"></sup>your claims are good and right, but no man listens to you on the part of the king.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Moreover, Absalom would say, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8394D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8394D\"></sup>Oh that one would appoint me judge in the land, then every man who has any suit or cause could come to me and I would give him justice.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And when a man came near to prostrate himself before him, he would put out his hand and take hold of him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8395E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8395E\"></sup>kiss him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In this manner Absalom dealt with all Israel who came to the king for judgment; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8396F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8396F\"></sup>so Absalom stole away the hearts of the men of Israel.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now it came about at the end of forty years that Absalom said to the king, “Please let me go and pay my vow which I have vowed to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8397G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8397G\"></sup>Hebron.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8398H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8398H\"></sup>vowed a vow while I was living at Geshur in Aram, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8398I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8398I\"></sup>If the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> shall indeed bring me back to Jerusalem, then I will serve the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.’”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The king said to him, “Go in peace.” So he arose and went to Hebron.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Absalom sent spies throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying, “As soon as you hear the sound of the trumpet, then you shall say, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8400J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8400J\"></sup>Absalom is king in Hebron.’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then two hundred men went with Absalom from Jerusalem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8401K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8401K\"></sup>who were invited and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8401L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8401L\"></sup>went innocently, and they did not know anything.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And Absalom sent for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8402M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8402M\"></sup>Ahithophel the Gilonite, David’s counselor, from his city <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8402N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8402N\"></sup>Giloh, while he was offering the sacrifices. And the conspiracy was strong, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8402O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8402O\"></sup>the people increased continually with Absalom.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then a messenger came to David, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8403P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8403P\"></sup>The hearts of the men of Israel are with Absalom.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David said to all his servants who were with him at Jerusalem, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8404Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8404Q\"></sup>Arise and let us flee, for <i>otherwise</i> none of us will escape from Absalom. Go in haste, or he will overtake us quickly and bring down calamity on us and strike the city with the edge of the sword.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then the king’s servants said to the king, “Behold, your servants <i>are ready to do</i> whatever my lord the king chooses.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the king went out and all his household with him. But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8406R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8406R\"></sup>the king left ten concubines to keep the house.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The king went out and all the people with him, and they stopped at the last house.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now all his servants passed on beside him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8408S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8408S\"></sup>all the Cherethites, all the Pelethites and all the Gittites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8408T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8408T\"></sup>six hundred men who had come with him from Gath, passed on before the king.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then the king said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8409U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8409U\"></sup>Ittai the Gittite, “Why will you also go with us? Return and remain with the king, for you are a foreigner and also an exile; <i>return</i> to your own place.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>You came <i>only</i> yesterday, and shall I today make you wander with us, while <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8410V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8410V\"></sup>I go where I will? Return and take back your brothers; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8410W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8410W\"></sup>mercy and truth be with you.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Ittai answered the king and said, “As the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and as my lord the king lives, surely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8411X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8411X\"></sup>wherever my lord the king may be, whether for death or for life, there also your servant will be.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Therefore David said to Ittai, “Go and pass over.” So Ittai the Gittite passed over with all his men and all the little ones who <i>were</i> with him.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>While all the country was weeping with a loud voice, all the people passed over. The king also passed over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8413Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8413Y\"></sup>the brook Kidron, and all the people passed over toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8413Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8413Z\"></sup>the way of the wilderness.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8414AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8414AA\"></sup>Zadok also <i>came</i>, and all the Levites with him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8414AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8414AB\"></sup>carrying the ark of the covenant of God. And they set down the ark of God, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8414AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8414AC\"></sup>Abiathar came up until all the people had finished passing from the city.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The king said to Zadok, “Return the ark of God to the city. If I find favor in the sight of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8415AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8415AD\"></sup>He will bring me back again and show me both it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8415AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8415AE\"></sup>His habitation.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>But if He should say thus, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8416AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8416AF\"></sup>I have no delight in you,’ behold, here I am, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8416AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8416AG\"></sup>let Him do to me as seems good to Him.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The king said also to Zadok the priest, “Are you <i>not</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8417AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8417AH\"></sup>a seer? Return to the city in peace and your <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8417AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8417AI\"></sup>two sons with you, your son Ahimaaz and Jonathan the son of Abiathar.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>See, I am going to wait <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8418AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8418AJ\"></sup>at the fords of the wilderness until word comes from you to inform me.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Therefore Zadok and Abiathar returned the ark of God to Jerusalem and remained there.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And David went up the ascent of the <i>Mount of</i> Olives, and wept as he went, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8420AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8420AK\"></sup>his head was covered and he walked <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8420AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8420AL\"></sup>barefoot. Then all the people who were with him each covered his head and went up weeping as they went.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now someone told David, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8421AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8421AM\"></sup>Ahithophel is among the conspirators with Absalom.” And David said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, I pray, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8421AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8421AN\"></sup>make the counsel of Ahithophel foolishness.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>It happened as David was coming to the summit, where God was worshiped, that behold, Hushai the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8422AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8422AO\"></sup>Archite met him with his coat torn and dust on his head.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>David said to him, “If you pass over with me, then you will be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8423AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8423AP\"></sup>a burden to me.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But if you return to the city, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8424AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8424AQ\"></sup>say to Absalom, ‘I will be your servant, O king; as I have been your father’s servant in time past, so I will now be your servant,’ then you can thwart the counsel of Ahithophel for me.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Are not Zadok and Abiathar the priests with you there? So it shall be that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8425AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8425AR\"></sup>whatever you hear from the king’s house, you shall report to Zadok and Abiathar the priests.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Behold <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8426AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8426AS\"></sup>their two sons are with them there, Ahimaaz, Zadok’s son and Jonathan, Abiathar’s son; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8426AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8426AT\"></sup>by them you shall send me everything that you hear.”",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>So Hushai, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8427AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8427AU\"></sup>David’s friend, came into the city, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8427AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8427AV\"></sup>Absalom came into Jerusalem."
		},
		"16": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">16 </span>Now when David had passed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8428A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8428A\"></sup>a little beyond the summit, behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8428B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8428B\"></sup>Ziba the servant of Mephibosheth met him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8428C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8428C\"></sup>with a couple of saddled donkeys, and on them <i>were</i> two hundred loaves of bread, a hundred clusters of raisins, a hundred summer fruits, and a jug of wine.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king said to Ziba, “Why do you have these?” And Ziba said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8429D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8429D\"></sup>The donkeys are for the king’s household to ride, and the bread and summer fruit for the young men to eat, and the wine, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8429E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8429E\"></sup>for whoever is faint in the wilderness to drink.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then the king said, “And where is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8430F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8430F\"></sup>your master’s son?” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8430G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8430G\"></sup>Ziba said to the king, “Behold, he is staying in Jerusalem, for he said, ‘Today the house of Israel will restore the kingdom of my father to me.’”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the king said to Ziba, “Behold, all that belongs to Mephibosheth is yours.” And Ziba said, “I prostrate myself; let me find favor in your sight, O my lord, the king!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>When King David came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8432H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8432H\"></sup>Bahurim, behold, there came out from there a man of the family of the house of Saul <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8432I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8432I\"></sup>whose name was Shimei, the son of Gera; he came out <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8432J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8432J\"></sup>cursing continually as he came.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>He threw stones at David and at all the servants of King David; and all the people and all the mighty men were at his right hand and at his left.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Thus Shimei said when he cursed, “Get out, get out, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8434K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8434K\"></sup>you man of bloodshed, and worthless fellow!",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8435L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8435L\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has returned upon you all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8435M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8435M\"></sup>the bloodshed of the house of Saul, in whose place you have reigned; and the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has given the kingdom into the hand of your son Absalom. And behold, you are <i>taken</i> in your own evil, for you are a man of bloodshed!”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8436N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8436N\"></sup>Abishai the son of Zeruiah said to the king, “Why should <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8436O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8436O\"></sup>this dead dog <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8436P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8436P\"></sup>curse my lord the king? Let me go over now and cut off his head.”",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But the king said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8437Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8437Q\"></sup>What have I to do with you, O sons of Zeruiah? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8437R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8437R\"></sup>If he curses, and if the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has told him, ‘Curse David,’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8437S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8437S\"></sup>then who shall say, ‘Why have you done so?’”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then David said to Abishai and to all his servants, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8438T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8438T\"></sup>my son who came out from me seeks my life; how much more now this Benjamite? Let him alone and let him curse, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8438U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8438U\"></sup>for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has told him.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Perhaps the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> will look on my affliction and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8439V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8439V\"></sup>return good to me instead of his cursing this day.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So David and his men went on the way; and Shimei went along on the hillside parallel with him and as he went he cursed and cast stones and threw dust at him.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The king and all the people who were with him arrived weary and he refreshed himself there.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8442W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8442W\"></sup>Then Absalom and all the people, the men of Israel, entered Jerusalem, and Ahithophel with him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now it came about when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8443X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8443X\"></sup>Hushai the Archite, David’s friend, came to Absalom, that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8443Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8443Y\"></sup>Hushai said to Absalom, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8443Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8443Z\"></sup><i>Long</i> live the king! <i>Long</i> live the king!”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Absalom said to Hushai, “Is this your loyalty to your friend? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8444AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8444AA\"></sup>Why did you not go with your friend?”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then Hushai said to Absalom, “No! For whom the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, this people, and all the men of Israel have chosen, his I will be, and with him I will remain.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Besides, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8446AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8446AB\"></sup>whom should I serve? <i>Should I</i> not <i>serve</i> in the presence of his son? As I have served in your father’s presence, so I will be in your presence.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Absalom said to Ahithophel, “Give your advice. What shall we do?”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Ahithophel said to Absalom, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8448AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8448AC\"></sup>Go in to your father’s concubines, whom he has left to keep the house; then all Israel will hear that you have made yourself odious to your father. The hands of all who are with you will also be strengthened.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>So they pitched a tent for Absalom on the roof, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8449AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8449AD\"></sup>and Absalom went in to his father’s concubines <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8449AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8449AE\"></sup>in the sight of all Israel.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8450AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8450AF\"></sup>The advice of Ahithophel, which he gave in those days, <i>was</i> as if one inquired of the word of God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8450AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8450AG\"></sup>so was all the advice of Ahithophel <i>regarded</i> by both David and Absalom."
		},
		"17": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">17 </span>Furthermore, Ahithophel said to Absalom, “Please let me choose 12,000 men that I may arise and pursue David tonight.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8452A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8452A\"></sup>I will come upon him while he is weary and exhausted and terrify him, so that all the people who are with him will flee. Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8452B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8452B\"></sup>I will strike down the king alone,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>and I will bring back all the people to you. The return of everyone depends on the man you seek; <i>then</i> all the people will be at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8453C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8453C\"></sup>peace.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>So the plan pleased Absalom and all the elders of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Absalom said, “Now call <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8455D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8455D\"></sup>Hushai the Archite also, and let us hear what he has to say.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>When Hushai had come to Absalom, Absalom said to him, “Ahithophel has spoken thus. Shall we carry out his plan? If not, you speak.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Hushai said to Absalom, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8457E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8457E\"></sup>This time the advice that Ahithophel has given is not good.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Moreover, Hushai said, “You know your father and his men, that they are mighty men and they are fierce, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8458F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8458F\"></sup>like a bear robbed of her cubs in the field. And your father is an expert in warfare, and will not spend the night with the people.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Behold, he has now hidden himself in one of the caves or in another place; and it will be when he falls on them at the first attack, that whoever hears <i>it</i> will say, ‘There has been a slaughter among the people who follow Absalom.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And even the one who is valiant, whose heart is like the heart of a lion, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8460G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8460G\"></sup>will completely lose heart; for all Israel knows that your father is a mighty man and those who are with him are valiant men.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But I counsel that all Israel be surely gathered to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8461H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8461H\"></sup>from Dan even to Beersheba, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8461I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8461I\"></sup>as the sand that is by the sea in abundance, and that you personally go into battle.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>So we shall come to him in one of the places where he can be found, and we will fall on him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8462J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8462J\"></sup>as the dew falls on the ground; and of him and of all the men who are with him, not even one will be left.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>If he withdraws into a city, then all Israel shall bring ropes to that city, and we will <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8463K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8463K\"></sup>drag it into the valley until not even a small stone is found there.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Absalom and all the men of Israel said, “The counsel of Hushai the Archite is better than the counsel of Ahithophel.” For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8464L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8464L\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had ordained to thwart the good counsel of Ahithophel, so that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> might bring calamity on Absalom.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8465M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8465M\"></sup>Hushai said to Zadok and to Abiathar the priests, “This is what Ahithophel counseled Absalom and the elders of Israel, and this is what I have counseled.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Now therefore, send quickly and tell David, saying, ‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8466N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8466N\"></sup>Do not spend the night at the fords of the wilderness, but by all means cross over, or else the king and all the people who are with him will be destroyed.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8467O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8467O\"></sup>Now Jonathan and Ahimaaz were staying at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8467P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8467P\"></sup>En-rogel, and a maidservant would go and tell them, and they would go and tell King David, for they could not be seen entering the city.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>But a lad did see them and told Absalom; so the two of them departed quickly and came to the house of a man <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8468Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8468Q\"></sup>in Bahurim, who had a well in his courtyard, and they went down into it.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8469R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8469R\"></sup>the woman took a covering and spread it over the well’s mouth and scattered grain on it, so that nothing was known.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then Absalom’s servants came to the woman at the house and said, “Where are Ahimaaz and Jonathan?” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8470S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8470S\"></sup>the woman said to them, “They have crossed the brook of water.” And when they searched and could not find <i>them</i>, they returned to Jerusalem.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>It came about after they had departed that they came up out of the well and went and told King David; and they said to David, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8471T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8471T\"></sup>Arise and cross over the water quickly for thus Ahithophel has counseled against you.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then David and all the people who <i>were</i> with him arose and crossed the Jordan; and by dawn not even one remained who had not crossed the Jordan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Now when Ahithophel saw that his counsel was not followed, he saddled <i>his</i> donkey and arose and went to his home, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8473U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8473U\"></sup>his city, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8473V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8473V\"></sup>set his house in order, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8473W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8473W\"></sup>strangled himself; thus he died and was buried in the grave of his father.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then David came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8474X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8474X\"></sup>Mahanaim. And Absalom crossed the Jordan, he and all the men of Israel with him.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Absalom set <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8475Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8475Y\"></sup>Amasa over the army in place of Joab. Now Amasa was the son of a man whose name was Ithra the Israelite, who went in to Abigail the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8475Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8475Z\"></sup>Nahash, sister of Zeruiah, Joab’s mother.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>And Israel and Absalom camped in the land of Gilead.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Now when David had come to Mahanaim, Shobi <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8477AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8477AA\"></sup>the son of Nahash from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8477AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8477AB\"></sup>Rabbah of the sons of Ammon, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8477AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8477AC\"></sup>Machir the son of Ammiel from Lo-debar, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8477AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8477AD\"></sup>Barzillai the Gileadite from Rogelim,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8478AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8478AE\"></sup>beds, basins, pottery, wheat, barley, flour, parched <i>grain</i>, beans, lentils, parched <i>seeds</i>,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>honey, curds, sheep, and cheese of the herd, for David and for the people who <i>were</i> with him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8479AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8479AF\"></sup>to eat; for they said, “The people are hungry and weary and thirsty in the wilderness.”"
		},
		"18": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">18 </span>Then David numbered the people who were with him and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8480A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8480A\"></sup>set over them commanders of thousands and commanders of hundreds.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>David sent the people out, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8481B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8481B\"></sup>one third under the command of Joab, one third under the command of Abishai the son of Zeruiah, Joab’s brother, and one third under the command of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8481C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8481C\"></sup>Ittai the Gittite. And the king said to the people, “I myself will surely go out with you also.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But the people said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8482D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8482D\"></sup>You should not go out; for if we indeed flee, they will not care about us; even if half of us die, they will not care about us. But you are worth ten thousand of us; therefore now it is better that you <i>be ready</i> to help us from the city.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king said to them, “Whatever seems best to you I will do.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8483E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8483E\"></sup>the king stood beside the gate, and all the people went out by hundreds and thousands.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>The king charged Joab and Abishai and Ittai, saying, “<i>Deal</i> gently for my sake with the young man Absalom.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8484F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8484F\"></sup>all the people heard when the king charged all the commanders concerning Absalom.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then the people went out into the field against Israel, and the battle took place in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8485G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8485G\"></sup>the forest of Ephraim.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The people of Israel were defeated there before the servants of David, and the slaughter there that day was great, 20,000 men.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>For the battle there was spread over the whole countryside, and the forest devoured more people that day than the sword devoured.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Now Absalom happened to meet the servants of David. For Absalom was riding on <i>his</i> mule, and the mule went under the thick branches of a great oak. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8488H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8488H\"></sup>his head caught fast in the oak, so he was left hanging between heaven and earth, while the mule that was under him kept going.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When a certain man saw <i>it</i>, he told Joab and said, “Behold, I saw Absalom hanging in an oak.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then Joab said to the man who had told him, “Now behold, you saw <i>him</i>! Why then did you not strike him there to the ground? And I would have given you ten <i>pieces</i> of silver and a belt.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The man said to Joab, “Even if I should receive a thousand <i>pieces of</i> silver in my hand, I would not put out my hand against the king’s son; for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8491I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8491I\"></sup>in our hearing the king charged you and Abishai and Ittai, saying, ‘Protect for me the young man Absalom!’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Otherwise, if I had dealt treacherously against his life (and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8492J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8492J\"></sup>there is nothing hidden from the king), then you yourself would have stood aloof.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then Joab said, “I will not waste time here with you.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8493K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8493K\"></sup>So he took three spears in his hand and thrust them through the heart of Absalom while he was yet alive in the midst of the oak.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And ten young men who carried Joab’s armor gathered around and struck Absalom and killed him.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8495L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8495L\"></sup>Joab blew the trumpet, and the people returned from pursuing Israel, for Joab restrained the people.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They took Absalom and cast him into a deep pit in the forest and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8496M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8496M\"></sup>erected over him a very great heap of stones. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8496N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8496N\"></sup>all Israel fled, each to his tent.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Now Absalom in his lifetime had taken and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8497O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8497O\"></sup>set up for himself a pillar which is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8497P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8497P\"></sup>the King’s Valley, for he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8497Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8497Q\"></sup>I have no son to preserve my name.” So he named the pillar after his own name, and it is called Absalom’s Monument to this day.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8498R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8498R\"></sup>Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said, “Please let me run and bring the king news <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8498S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8498S\"></sup>that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has freed him from the hand of his enemies.”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>But Joab said to him, “You are not the man to carry news this day, but you shall carry news another day; however, you shall carry no news today because the king’s son is dead.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Joab said to the Cushite, “Go, tell the king what you have seen.” So the Cushite bowed to Joab and ran.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Now Ahimaaz the son of Zadok said once more to Joab, “But whatever happens, please let me also run after the Cushite.” And Joab said, “Why would you run, my son, since <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8501T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8501T\"></sup>you will have no reward for going?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“But whatever happens,” <i>he said</i>, “I will run.” So he said to him, “Run.” Then Ahimaaz ran by way of the plain and passed up the Cushite.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8503U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8503U\"></sup>David was sitting between the two gates; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8503V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8503V\"></sup>the watchman went up to the roof of the gate by the wall, and raised his eyes and looked, and behold, a man running by himself.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The watchman called and told the king. And the king said, “If he is by himself there is good news in his mouth.” And he came nearer and nearer.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Then the watchman saw another man running; and the watchman called to the gatekeeper and said, “Behold, <i>another</i> man running by himself.” And the king said, “This one also is bringing good news.”",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The watchman said, “I think the running of the first one <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8506W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8506W\"></sup>is like the running of Ahimaaz the son of Zadok.” And the king said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8506X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8506X\"></sup>This is a good man and comes with good news.”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Ahimaaz called and said to the king, “All is well.” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8507Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8507Y\"></sup>he prostrated himself before the king with his face to the ground. And he said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8507Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8507Z\"></sup>Blessed is the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God, who has delivered up the men who lifted their hands against my lord the king.”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The king said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8508AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8508AA\"></sup>Is it well with the young man Absalom?” And Ahimaaz answered, “When Joab sent the king’s servant, and your servant, I saw a great tumult, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8508AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8508AB\"></sup>I did not know what <i>it was</i>.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then the king said, “Turn aside and stand here.” So he turned aside and stood still.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Behold, the Cushite arrived, and the Cushite said, “Let my lord the king receive good news, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8510AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8510AC\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has freed you this day from the hand of all those who rose up against you.”",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Then the king said to the Cushite, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8511AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8511AD\"></sup>Is it well with the young man Absalom?” And the Cushite answered, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8511AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8511AE\"></sup>Let the enemies of my lord the king, and all who rise up against you for evil, be as that young man!”",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The king was deeply moved and went up to the chamber over the gate and wept. And thus he said as he walked, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8512AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8512AF\"></sup>O my son Absalom, my son, my son Absalom! <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8512AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8512AG\"></sup>Would I had died instead of you, O Absalom, my son, my son!”"
		},
		"19": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">19 </span>Then it was told Joab, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8513A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8513A\"></sup>the king is weeping and mourns for Absalom.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The victory that day was turned to mourning for all the people, for the people heard <i>it</i> said that day, “The king is grieved for his son.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>So the people went by stealth into the city that day, as people who are humiliated steal away when they flee in battle.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The king <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8516B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8516B\"></sup>covered his face and cried out with a loud voice, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8516C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8516C\"></sup>O my son Absalom, O Absalom, my son, my son!”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then Joab came into the house to the king and said, “Today you have covered with shame the faces of all your servants, who today have saved your life and the lives of your sons and daughters, the lives of your wives, and the lives of your concubines,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>by loving those who hate you, and by hating those who love you. For you have shown today that princes and servants are nothing to you; for I know this day that if Absalom were alive and all of us were dead today, then you would be pleased.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Now therefore arise, go out and speak kindly to your servants, for I swear by the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, if you do not go out, surely <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8519D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8519D\"></sup>not a man will pass the night with you, and this will be worse for you than all the evil that has come upon you from your youth until now.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the king arose and sat in the gate. When they told all the people, saying, “Behold, the king is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8520E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8520E\"></sup>sitting in the gate,” then all the people came before the king.Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8520F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8520F\"></sup>Israel had fled, each to his tent.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>All the people were quarreling throughout all the tribes of Israel, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8521G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8521G\"></sup>The king delivered us from the hand of our enemies and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8521H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8521H\"></sup>saved us from the hand of the Philistines, but now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8521I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8521I\"></sup>he has fled out of the land from Absalom.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>However, Absalom, whom we anointed over us, has died in battle. Now then, why are you silent about bringing the king back?”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Then King David sent to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8523J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8523J\"></sup>Zadok and Abiathar the priests, saying, “Speak to the elders of Judah, saying, ‘Why are you the last to bring the king back to his house, since the word of all Israel has come to the king, <i>even</i> to his house?",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>You are my brothers; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8524K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8524K\"></sup>you are my bone and my flesh. Why then should you be the last to bring back the king?’",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Say to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8525L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8525L\"></sup>Amasa, ‘Are you not my bone and my flesh? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8525M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8525M\"></sup>May God do so to me, and more also, if you will not be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8525N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8525N\"></sup>commander of the army before me continually <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8525O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8525O\"></sup>in place of Joab.’”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Thus he turned the hearts of all the men of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8526P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8526P\"></sup>as one man, so that they sent <i>word</i> to the king, <i>saying</i>, “Return, you and all your servants.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The king then returned and came as far as the Jordan. And Judah came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8527Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8527Q\"></sup>Gilgal in order to go to meet the king, to bring the king across the Jordan.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8528R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8528R\"></sup>Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjamite who was from Bahurim, hurried and came down with the men of Judah to meet King David.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>There were a thousand men of Benjamin with him, with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8529S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8529S\"></sup>Ziba the servant of the house of Saul, and his fifteen sons and his twenty servants with him; and they rushed to the Jordan before the king.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then they kept crossing the ford to bring over the king’s household, and to do what was good in his sight. And Shimei the son of Gera fell down before the king as he was about to cross the Jordan.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>So he said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8531T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8531T\"></sup>Let not my lord consider me guilty, nor remember what your servant did wrong on the day when my lord the king came out from Jerusalem, so that the king would take <i>it</i> to heart.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>For your servant knows that I have sinned; therefore behold, I have come today, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8532U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8532U\"></sup>the first of all the house of Joseph to go down to meet my lord the king.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>But Abishai the son of Zeruiah said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8533V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8533V\"></sup>Should not Shimei be put to death for this, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8533W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8533W\"></sup>because he cursed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord’s</span> anointed?”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>David then said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8534X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8534X\"></sup>What have I to do with you, O sons of Zeruiah, that you should this day be an adversary to me? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8534Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8534Y\"></sup>Should any man be put to death in Israel today? For do I not know that I am king over Israel today?”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The king said to Shimei, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8535Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8535Z\"></sup>You shall not die.” Thus the king swore to him.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8536AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8536AA\"></sup>Mephibosheth the son of Saul came down to meet the king; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8536AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8536AB\"></sup>he had neither cared for his feet, nor trimmed his mustache, nor <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8536AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8536AC\"></sup>washed his clothes, from the day the king departed until the day he came <i>home</i> in peace.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>It was when he came from Jerusalem to meet the king, that the king said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8537AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8537AD\"></sup>Why did you not go with me, Mephibosheth?”",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>So he answered, “O my lord, the king, my servant deceived me; for your servant said, ‘I will saddle a donkey for myself that I may ride on it and go with the king,’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8538AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8538AE\"></sup>because your servant is lame.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Moreover, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8539AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8539AF\"></sup>he has slandered your servant to my lord the king; but my lord the king is <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8539AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8539AG\"></sup>like the angel of God, therefore do what is good in your sight.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8540AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8540AH\"></sup>all my father’s household was nothing but dead men before my lord the king; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8540AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8540AI\"></sup>yet you set your servant among those who ate at your own table. What right do I have yet that I should complain anymore to the king?”",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>So the king said to him, “Why do you still speak of your affairs? I have decided, ‘You and Ziba shall divide the land.’”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Mephibosheth said to the king, “Let him even take it all, since my lord the king has come safely to his own house.”",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8543AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8543AJ\"></sup>Barzillai the Gileadite had come down from Rogelim; and he went on to the Jordan with the king to escort him over the Jordan.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Now Barzillai was very old, being eighty years old; and he had <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8544AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8544AK\"></sup>sustained the king while he stayed at Mahanaim, for he was a very great man.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The king said to Barzillai, “You cross over with me and I will sustain you in Jerusalem with me.”",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>But Barzillai said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8546AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8546AL\"></sup>How long have I yet to live, that I should go up with the king to Jerusalem?",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>I am now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8547AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8547AM\"></sup>eighty years old. Can I distinguish between good and bad? Or can your servant taste what I eat or what I drink? Or can I hear anymore <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8547AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8547AN\"></sup>the voice of singing men and women? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8547AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8547AO\"></sup>Why then should your servant be an added burden to my lord the king?",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Your servant would merely cross over the Jordan with the king. Why should the king compensate me <i>with</i> this reward?",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Please let your servant return, that I may die in my own city near the grave of my father and my mother. However, here is your servant <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8549AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8549AP\"></sup>Chimham, let him cross over with my lord the king, and do for him what is good in your sight.”",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The king answered, “Chimham shall cross over with me, and I will do for him what is good in your sight; and whatever you require of me, I will do for you.”",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>All the people crossed over the Jordan and the king crossed too. The king then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8551AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8551AQ\"></sup>kissed Barzillai and blessed him, and he returned to his place.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Now the king went on to Gilgal, and Chimham went on with him; and all the people of Judah and also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8552AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8552AR\"></sup>half the people of Israel accompanied the king.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>And behold, all the men of Israel came to the king and said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8553AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8553AS\"></sup>Why had our brothers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8553AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8553AT\"></sup>the men of Judah stolen you away, and brought the king and his household and all David’s men with him over the Jordan?”",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Then all the men of Judah answered the men of Israel, “Because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8554AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8554AU\"></sup>the king is a close relative to us. Why then are you angry about this matter? Have we eaten at all at the king’s <i>expense</i>, or has anything been taken for us?”",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>But the men of Israel answered the men of Judah and said, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8555AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8555AV\"></sup>We have ten parts in the king, therefore we also have more <i>claim</i> on David than you. Why then did you treat us with contempt? Was it not our advice first to bring back our king?” Yet the words of the men of Judah were harsher than the words of the men of Israel."
		},
		"20": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">20 </span>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8556A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8556A\"></sup>a worthless fellow happened to be there whose name was Sheba, the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8556B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8556B\"></sup>Bichri, a Benjamite; and he blew the trumpet and said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8556C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8556C\"></sup>We have no portion in David,Nor do we have inheritance in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8556D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8556D\"></sup>the son of Jesse;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8556E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8556E\"></sup>Every man to his tents, O Israel!”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So all the men of Israel withdrew from following David <i>and</i> followed Sheba the son of Bichri; but the men of Judah remained steadfast to their king, from the Jordan even to Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Then David came to his house at Jerusalem, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8558F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8558F\"></sup>the king took the ten women, the concubines whom he had left to keep the house, and placed them under guard and provided them with sustenance, but did not go in to them. So they were shut up until the day of their death, living as widows.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8559G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8559G\"></sup>Amasa, “Call out the men of Judah for me within three days, and be present here yourself.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So Amasa went to call out <i>the men of</i> Judah, but he <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8560H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8560H\"></sup>delayed longer than the set time which he had appointed him.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And David said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8561I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8561I\"></sup>Abishai, “Now Sheba the son of Bichri will do us more harm than Absalom; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8561J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8561J\"></sup>take your lord’s servants and pursue him, so that he does not find for himself fortified cities and escape from our sight.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>So Joab’s men went out after him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8562K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8562K\"></sup>along with the Cherethites and the Pelethites and all the mighty men; and they went out from Jerusalem to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>When they were at the large stone which is in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8563L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8563L\"></sup>Gibeon, Amasa came to meet them. Now Joab was dressed in his military attire, and over it was a belt with a sword in its sheath fastened at his waist; and as he went forward, it fell out.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joab said to Amasa, “Is it well with you, my brother?” And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8564M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8564M\"></sup>Joab took Amasa by the beard with his right hand to kiss him.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But Amasa was not on guard against the sword which was in Joab’s hand so <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8565N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8565N\"></sup>he struck him in the belly with it and poured out his inward parts on the ground, and did not <i>strike</i> him again, and he died. Then Joab and Abishai his brother pursued Sheba the son of Bichri.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now there stood by him one of Joab’s young men, and said, “Whoever favors Joab and whoever is for David, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8566O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8566O\"></sup><i>let him</i> follow Joab.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But Amasa lay wallowing in <i>his</i> blood in the middle of the highway. And when the man saw that all the people stood still, he removed Amasa from the highway into the field and threw a garment over him when he saw that everyone who came by him stood still.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>As soon as he was removed from the highway, all the men passed on after Joab to pursue Sheba the son of Bichri.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now he went through all the tribes of Israel to Abel, even Beth-maacah, and all the Berites; and they were gathered together and also went after him.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>They came and besieged him in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8570P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8570P\"></sup>Abel Beth-maacah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8570Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8570Q\"></sup>they cast up a siege ramp against the city, and it stood by the rampart; and all the people who were with Joab were wreaking destruction in order to topple the wall.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8571R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8571R\"></sup>a wise woman called from the city, “Hear, hear! Please tell Joab, ‘Come here that I may speak with you.’”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>So he approached her, and the woman said, “Are you Joab?” And he answered, “I am.” Then she said to him, “Listen to the words of your maidservant.” And he answered, “I am listening.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Then she spoke, saying, “Formerly they used to say, ‘They will surely ask <i>advice</i> at Abel,’ and thus they ended <i>the dispute</i>.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I am of those who are peaceable <i>and</i> faithful in Israel. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8574S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8574S\"></sup>You are seeking to destroy a city, even a mother in Israel. Why would you swallow up <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8574T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8574T\"></sup>the inheritance of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Joab replied, “Far be it, far be it from me that I should swallow up or destroy!",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Such is not the case. But a man from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8576U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8576U\"></sup>the hill country of Ephraim, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8576V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8576V\"></sup>Sheba the son of Bichri by name, has lifted up his hand against King David. Only hand him over, and I will depart from the city.” And the woman said to Joab, “Behold, his head will be thrown to you over the wall.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then the woman <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8577W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8577W\"></sup>wisely came to all the people. And they cut off the head of Sheba the son of Bichri and threw it to Joab. So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8577X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8577X\"></sup>he blew the trumpet, and they were dispersed from the city, each to his tent. Joab also returned to the king at Jerusalem.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8578Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8578Y\"></sup>Now Joab was over the whole army of Israel, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was over the Cherethites and the Pelethites;",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>and Adoram was over the forced labor, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8579Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8579Z\"></sup>Jehoshaphat the son of Ahilud was the recorder;",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and Sheva was scribe, and Zadok and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8580AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8580AA\"></sup>Abiathar were priests;",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and Ira the Jairite was also a priest to David."
		},
		"21": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">21 </span>Now there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8582A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8582A\"></sup>a famine in the days of David for three years, year after year; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8582B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8582B\"></sup>David sought the presence of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> said, “It is for Saul and his bloody house, because he put the Gibeonites to death.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So the king called the Gibeonites and spoke to them (now the Gibeonites were not of the sons of Israel but of the remnant of the Amorites, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8583C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8583C\"></sup>the sons of Israel made a covenant with them, but Saul had sought to kill them in his zeal for the sons of Israel and Judah).",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Thus David said to the Gibeonites, “What should I do for you? And how can I make atonement that you may bless <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8584D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8584D\"></sup>the inheritance of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the Gibeonites said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8585E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8585E\"></sup>We have no <i>concern</i> of silver or gold with Saul or his house, nor is it for us to put any man to death in Israel.” And he said, “I will do for you whatever you say.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So they said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8586F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8586F\"></sup>The man who consumed us and who planned to exterminate us from remaining within any border of Israel,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>let seven men from his sons be given to us, and we will hang them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8587G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8587G\"></sup>before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Gibeah of Saul, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8587H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8587H\"></sup>the chosen of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.” And the king said, “I will give <i>them</i>.”",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But the king spared <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8588I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8588I\"></sup>Mephibosheth, the son of Jonathan the son of Saul, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8588J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8588J\"></sup>because of the oath of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> which was between them, between David and Saul’s son Jonathan.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So the king took the two sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8589K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8589K\"></sup>Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, Armoni and Mephibosheth whom she had borne to Saul, and the five sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8589L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8589L\"></sup>Merab the daughter of Saul, whom she had borne to Adriel the son of Barzillai the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8589M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8589M\"></sup>Meholathite.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then he gave them into the hands of the Gibeonites, and they hanged them in the mountain before the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, so that the seven of them fell together; and they were put to death in the first days of harvest at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8590N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8590N\"></sup>the beginning of barley harvest.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8591O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8591O\"></sup>And Rizpah the daughter of Aiah took sackcloth and spread it for herself on the rock, from the beginning of harvest until it rained on them from the sky; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8591P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8591P\"></sup>she allowed neither the birds of the sky to rest on them by day nor the beasts of the field by night.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When it was told David what Rizpah the daughter of Aiah, the concubine of Saul, had done,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>then David went and took <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8593Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8593Q\"></sup>the bones of Saul and the bones of Jonathan his son from the men of Jabesh-gilead, who had stolen them from the open square of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8593R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8593R\"></sup>Beth-shan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8593S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8593S\"></sup>where the Philistines had hanged them on the day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8593T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8593T\"></sup>the Philistines struck down Saul in Gilboa.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>He brought up the bones of Saul and the bones of Jonathan his son from there, and they gathered the bones of those who had been hanged.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>They buried the bones of Saul and Jonathan his son in the country of Benjamin in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8595U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8595U\"></sup>Zela, in the grave of Kish his father; thus they did all that the king commanded, and after that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8595V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8595V\"></sup>God was moved by prayer for the land.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8596W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8596W\"></sup>the Philistines were at war again with Israel, David went down and his servants with him; and as they fought against the Philistines, David became weary.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then Ishbi-benob, who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8597X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8597X\"></sup>among the descendants of the giant, the weight of whose spear was three hundred <i>shekels</i> of bronze in weight, was girded with a new <i>sword</i>, and he intended to kill David.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>But <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8598Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8598Y\"></sup>Abishai the son of Zeruiah helped him, and struck the Philistine and killed him. Then the men of David swore to him, saying, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8598Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8598Z\"></sup>You shall not go out again with us to battle, so that you do not extinguish <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8598AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8598AA\"></sup>the lamp of Israel.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8599AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8599AB\"></sup>Now it came about after this that there was war again with the Philistines at Gob; then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8599AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8599AC\"></sup>Sibbecai the Hushathite struck down Saph, who was among the descendants of the giant.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>There was war with the Philistines again at Gob, and Elhanan the son of Jaare-oregim the Bethlehemite killed Goliath the Gittite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8600AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8600AD\"></sup>the shaft of whose spear was like a weaver’s beam.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>There was war at Gath again, where there was a man of <i>great</i> stature who had six fingers on each hand and six toes on each foot, twenty-four in number; and he also had been born <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8601AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8601AE\"></sup>to the giant.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>When he defied Israel, Jonathan the son of Shimei, David’s brother, struck him down.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8603AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8603AF\"></sup>These four were born to the giant in Gath, and they fell by the hand of David and by the hand of his servants."
		},
		"22": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">22 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8604A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8604A\"></sup>And David spoke <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8604B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8604B\"></sup>the words of this song to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in the day that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> delivered him from the hand of all his enemies and from the hand of Saul.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>He said,“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8605C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8605C\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is my rock and my fortress and my deliverer;",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8606D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8606D\"></sup>My God, my rock, in whom I take refuge,My <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8606E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8606E\"></sup>shield and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8606F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8606F\"></sup>the horn of my salvation, my stronghold and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8606G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8606G\"></sup>my refuge;My savior, You save me from violence.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>“I call upon the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8607H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8607H\"></sup>who is worthy to be praised,And I am saved from my enemies.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8608I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8608I\"></sup>the waves of death encompassed me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8608J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8608J\"></sup>The torrents of destruction overwhelmed me;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8609K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8609K\"></sup>The cords of Sheol surrounded me;The snares of death confronted me.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8610L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8610L\"></sup>In my distress I called upon the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,Yes, I cried to my God;And from His temple He heard my voice,And my cry for help <i>came</i> into His ears.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8611M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8611M\"></sup>the earth shook and quaked,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8611N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8611N\"></sup>The foundations of heaven were tremblingAnd were shaken, because He was angry.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>“Smoke went up out of His nostrils,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8612O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8612O\"></sup>Fire from His mouth devoured;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8612P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8612P\"></sup>Coals were kindled by it.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“He bowed the heavens also, and came downWith <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8613Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8613Q\"></sup>thick darkness under His feet.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8614R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8614R\"></sup>And He rode on a cherub and flew;And He appeared on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8614S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8614S\"></sup>the wings of the wind.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8615T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8615T\"></sup>And He made darkness canopies around Him,A mass of waters, thick clouds of the sky.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“From the brightness before Him<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8616U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8616U\"></sup>Coals of fire were kindled.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8617V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8617V\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> thundered from heaven,And the Most High uttered His voice.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8618W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8618W\"></sup>And He sent out arrows, and scattered them,Lightning, and routed them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“Then the channels of the sea appeared,The foundations of the world were laid bareBy the rebuke of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8619X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8619X\"></sup>At the blast of the breath of His nostrils.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8620Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8620Y\"></sup>He sent from on high, He took me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8620Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8620Z\"></sup>He drew me out of many waters.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>“He delivered me from my strong enemy,From those who hated me, for they were too strong for me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>“They confronted me in the day of my calamity,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8622AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8622AA\"></sup>But the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was my support.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8623AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8623AB\"></sup>He also brought me forth into a broad place;He rescued me, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8623AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8623AC\"></sup>because He delighted in me.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8624AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8624AD\"></sup>The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has rewarded me according to my righteousness;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8624AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8624AE\"></sup>According to the cleanness of my hands He has recompensed me.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8625AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8625AF\"></sup>For I have kept the ways of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,And have not acted wickedly against my God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8626AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8626AG\"></sup>For all His ordinances <i>were</i> before me,And <i>as for</i> His statutes, I did not depart from them.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8627AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8627AH\"></sup>I was also blameless toward Him,And I kept myself from my iniquity.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8628AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8628AI\"></sup>Therefore the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> has recompensed me according to my righteousness,According to my cleanness before His eyes.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8629AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8629AJ\"></sup>With the kind You show Yourself kind,With the blameless You show Yourself blameless;",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8630AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8630AK\"></sup>With the pure You show Yourself pure,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8630AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8630AL\"></sup>And with the perverted You show Yourself astute.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8631AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8631AM\"></sup>And You save an afflicted people;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8631AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8631AN\"></sup>But Your eyes are on the haughty <i>whom</i> You abase.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8632AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8632AO\"></sup>For You are my lamp, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;And the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> illumines my darkness.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8633AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8633AP\"></sup>For by You I can run upon a troop;By my God I can leap over a wall.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8634AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8634AQ\"></sup>As for God, His way is blameless;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8634AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8634AR\"></sup>The word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is tested;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8634AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8634AS\"></sup>He is a shield to all who take refuge in Him.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8635AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8635AT\"></sup>For who is God, besides the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8635AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8635AU\"></sup>And who is a rock, besides our God?",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8636AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8636AV\"></sup>God is my strong fortress;And He sets the blameless in His way.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8637AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8637AW\"></sup>He makes my feet like hinds’ <i>feet</i>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8637AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8637AX\"></sup>And sets me on my high places.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8638AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8638AY\"></sup>He trains my hands for battle,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8638AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8638AZ\"></sup>So that my arms can bend a bow of bronze.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>“You have also given me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8639BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8639BA\"></sup>the shield of Your salvation,And Your help makes me great.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8640BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8640BB\"></sup>You enlarge my steps under me,And my feet have not slipped.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>“I pursued my enemies and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8641BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8641BC\"></sup>destroyed them,And I did not turn back until they were consumed.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>“And I have devoured them and shattered them, so that they did not rise;And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8642BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8642BD\"></sup>they fell under my feet.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>“For You have girded me with strength for battle;You have subdued under me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8643BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8643BE\"></sup>those who rose up against me.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>“You have also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8644BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8644BF\"></sup>made my enemies turn <i>their</i> backs to me,And I destroyed those who hated me.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8645BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8645BG\"></sup>They looked, but there was none to save;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8645BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8645BH\"></sup><i>Even</i> to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, but He did not answer them.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8646BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8646BI\"></sup>Then I pulverized them as the dust of the earth;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8646BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8646BJ\"></sup>I crushed <i>and</i> stamped them as the mire of the streets.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8647BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8647BK\"></sup>You have also delivered me from the contentions of my people;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8647BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8647BL\"></sup>You have kept me as head of the nations;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8647BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8647BM\"></sup>A people whom I have not known serve me.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8648BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8648BN\"></sup>Foreigners pretend obedience to me;As soon as they hear, they obey me.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>“Foreigners lose heart,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8649BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8649BO\"></sup>And come trembling out of their fortresses.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>“The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> lives, and blessed be my rock;And exalted be <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8650BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8650BP\"></sup>God, the rock of my salvation,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8651BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8651BQ\"></sup>The God who executes vengeance for me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8651BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8651BR\"></sup>And brings down peoples under me,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>Who also brings me out from my enemies;You even lift me above <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8652BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8652BS\"></sup>those who rise up against me;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8652BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8652BT\"></sup>You rescue me from the violent man.",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8653BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8653BU\"></sup>Therefore I will give thanks to You, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, among the nations,And I will sing praises to Your name.",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8654BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8654BV\"></sup><i>He</i> is a tower of deliverance to His king,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8654BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8654BW\"></sup>shows lovingkindness to His anointed,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8654BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8654BX\"></sup>To David and his descendants forever.”"
		},
		"23": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">23 </span>Now these are the last words of David.David the son of Jesse declares,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8655A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8655A\"></sup>The man who was raised on high declares,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8655B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8655B\"></sup>The anointed of the God of Jacob,And the sweet psalmist of Israel,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8656C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8656C\"></sup>The Spirit of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoke by me,And His word was on my tongue.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>“The God of Israel said,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8657D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8657D\"></sup>The Rock of Israel spoke to me,‘<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8657E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8657E\"></sup>He who rules over men righteously,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8657F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8657F\"></sup>Who rules in the fear of God,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8658G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8658G\"></sup>Is as the light of the morning <i>when</i> the sun rises,A morning without clouds,<i>When</i> the tender grass <i>springs</i> out of the earth,Through sunshine after rain.’",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>“Truly is not my house so with God?For <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8659H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8659H\"></sup>He has made an everlasting covenant with me,Ordered in all things, and secured;For all my salvation and all <i>my</i> desire,Will He not indeed make <i>it</i> grow?",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>“<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8660I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8660I\"></sup>But the worthless, every one of them will be thrust away like thorns,Because they cannot be taken in hand;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>But the man who touches themMust be armed with iron and the shaft of a spear,And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8661J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8661J\"></sup>they will be completely burned with fire in <i>their</i> place.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8662K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8662K\"></sup>These are the names of the mighty men whom David had: Josheb-basshebeth a Tahchemonite, chief of the captains, he was <i>called</i> Adino the Eznite, because of eight hundred slain <i>by him</i> at one time;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>and after him was Eleazar the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8663L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8663L\"></sup>Dodo the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8663M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8663M\"></sup>Ahohite, one of the three mighty men with David when they defied the Philistines who were gathered there to battle and the men of Israel had withdrawn.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8664N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8664N\"></sup>He arose and struck the Philistines until his hand was weary and clung to the sword, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8664O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8664O\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought about a great victory that day; and the people returned after him only to strip <i>the slain</i>.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now after him was Shammah the son of Agee a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8665P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8665P\"></sup>Hararite. And the Philistines were gathered into a troop where there was a plot of ground full of lentils, and the people fled from the Philistines.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But he took his stand in the midst of the plot, defended it and struck the Philistines; and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8666Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8666Q\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> brought about a great victory.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then three of the thirty chief men went down and came to David in the harvest time to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8667R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8667R\"></sup>cave of Adullam, while the troop of the Philistines was camping in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8667S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8667S\"></sup>the valley of Rephaim.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>David was then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8668T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8668T\"></sup>in the stronghold, while the garrison of the Philistines was then in Bethlehem.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8669U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8669U\"></sup>David had a craving and said, “Oh that someone would give me water to drink from the well of Bethlehem which is by the gate!”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8670V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8670V\"></sup>So the three mighty men broke through the camp of the Philistines, and drew water from the well of Bethlehem which was by the gate, and took <i>it</i> and brought <i>it</i> to David. Nevertheless he would not drink it, but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8670W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8670W\"></sup>poured it out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and he said, “Be it far from me, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, that I should do this. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8671X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8671X\"></sup><i>Shall I drink</i> the blood of the men who went in <i>jeopardy</i> of their lives?” Therefore he would not drink it. These things the three mighty men did.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8672Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8672Y\"></sup>Abishai, the brother of Joab, the son of Zeruiah, was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8672Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8672Z\"></sup>chief of the thirty. And he swung his spear against three hundred and killed <i>them</i>, and had a name as well as the three.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>He was most honored of the thirty, therefore he became their commander; however, he did not attain to the three.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8674AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8674AA\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, the son of a valiant man of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8674AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8674AB\"></sup>Kabzeel, who had done mighty deeds, killed the two <i>sons of</i> Ariel of Moab. He also went down and killed a lion in the middle of a pit on a snowy day.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>He killed an Egyptian, an impressive man. Now the Egyptian <i>had</i> a spear in his hand, but he went down to him with a club and snatched the spear from the Egyptian’s hand and killed him with his own spear.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>These <i>things</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8676AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8676AC\"></sup>Benaiah the son of Jehoiada did, and had a name as well as the three mighty men.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>He was honored among the thirty, but he did not attain to the three. And David appointed him over his guard.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8678AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8678AD\"></sup>Asahel the brother of Joab was among the thirty; Elhanan the son of Dodo of Bethlehem,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8679AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8679AE\"></sup>Shammah the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8679AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8679AF\"></sup>Harodite, Elika the Harodite,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Helez the Paltite, Ira the son of Ikkesh the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8680AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8680AG\"></sup>Tekoite,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Abiezer the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8681AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8681AH\"></sup>Anathothite, Mebunnai the Hushathite,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Zalmon the Ahohite, Maharai the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8682AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8682AI\"></sup>Netophathite,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8683AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8683AJ\"></sup>Heleb the son of Baanah the Netophathite, Ittai the son of Ribai of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8683AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8683AK\"></sup>Gibeah of the sons of Benjamin,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Benaiah a <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8684AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8684AL\"></sup>Pirathonite, Hiddai of the brooks of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8684AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8684AM\"></sup>Gaash,",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Abi-albon the Arbathite, Azmaveth the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8685AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8685AN\"></sup>Barhumite,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Eliahba the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8686AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8686AO\"></sup>Shaalbonite, the sons of Jashen, Jonathan,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8687AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8687AP\"></sup>Shammah the Hararite, Ahiam the son of Sharar the Ararite,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Eliphelet the son of Ahasbai, the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8688AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8688AQ\"></sup>the Maacathite, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8688AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8688AR\"></sup>Eliam the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8688AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8688AS\"></sup>Ahithophel the Gilonite,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8689AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8689AT\"></sup>Hezro the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8689AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8689AU\"></sup>Carmelite, Paarai the Arbite,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Igal the son of Nathan of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8690AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8690AV\"></sup>Zobah, Bani the Gadite,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Zelek the Ammonite, Naharai the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8691AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8691AW\"></sup>Beerothite, armor bearers of Joab the son of Zeruiah,",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>Ira the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8692AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8692AX\"></sup>Ithrite, Gareb the Ithrite,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8693AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8693AY\"></sup>Uriah the Hittite; thirty-seven in all."
		},
		"24": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">24 </span><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8694A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8694A\"></sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8694B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8694B\"></sup>again the anger of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> burned against Israel, and it incited David against them to say, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8694C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8694C\"></sup>Go, number Israel and Judah.”",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>The king said to Joab the commander of the army who was with him, “Go about now through all the tribes of Israel, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8695D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8695D\"></sup>from Dan to Beersheba, and register the people, that I may know the number of the people.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Joab said to the king, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8696E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8696E\"></sup>Now may the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God add to the people a hundred times as many as they are, while the eyes of my lord the king <i>still</i> see; but why does my lord the king delight in this thing?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Nevertheless, the king’s word prevailed against Joab and against the commanders of the army. So Joab and the commanders of the army went out from the presence of the king to register the people of Israel.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They crossed the Jordan and camped in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8698F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8698F\"></sup>Aroer, on the right side of the city that is in the middle of the valley of Gad and toward <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8698G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8698G\"></sup>Jazer.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then they came to Gilead and to the land of Tahtim-hodshi, and they came to Dan-jaan and around to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8699H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8699H\"></sup>Sidon,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and came to the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8700I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8700I\"></sup>fortress of Tyre and to all the cities of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8700J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8700J\"></sup>Hivites and of the Canaanites, and they went out to the south of Judah, <i>to</i> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8700K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8700K\"></sup>Beersheba.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>So when they had gone about through the whole land, they came to Jerusalem at the end of nine months and twenty days.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Joab gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8702L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8702L\"></sup>the number of the registration of the people to the king; and there were in Israel <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8702M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8702M\"></sup>eight hundred thousand valiant men who drew the sword, and the men of Judah were five hundred thousand men.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8703N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8703N\"></sup>David’s heart troubled him after he had numbered the people. So David said to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8703O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8703O\"></sup>I have sinned greatly in what I have done. But now, O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, please take away the iniquity of Your servant, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8703P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8703P\"></sup>I have acted very foolishly.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>When David arose in the morning, the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8704Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8704Q\"></sup>the prophet Gad, David’s <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8704R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8704R\"></sup>seer, saying,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>“Go and speak to David, ‘Thus the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> says, “I am offering you three things; choose for yourself one of them, which I will do to you.”’”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So Gad came to David and told him, and said to him, “Shall <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8706S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8706S\"></sup>seven years of famine come to you in your land? Or will you flee three months before your foes while they pursue you? Or shall there be three days’ pestilence in your land? Now consider and see what answer I shall return to Him who sent me.”",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then David said to Gad, “I am in great distress. Let us now fall into the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8707T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8707T\"></sup>for His mercies are great, but do not let me fall into the hand of man.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8708U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8708U\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> sent a pestilence upon Israel from the morning until the appointed time, and seventy thousand men of the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8708V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8708V\"></sup>from Dan to Beersheba died.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8709W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8709W\"></sup>When the angel stretched out his hand toward Jerusalem to destroy it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8709X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8709X\"></sup>the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> relented from the calamity and said to the angel who destroyed the people, “It is enough! Now relax your hand!” And the angel of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was by the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then David spoke to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> when he saw the angel who was striking down the people, and said, “Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8710Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8710Y\"></sup>it is I who have sinned, and it is I who have done wrong; but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8710Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8710Z\"></sup>these sheep, what have they done? Please let Your hand be against me and against my father’s house.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>So Gad came to David that day and said to him, “<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8711AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8711AA\"></sup>Go up, erect an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> on the threshing floor of Araunah the Jebusite.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>David went up according to the word of Gad, just as the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Araunah looked down and saw the king and his servants crossing over toward him; and Araunah went out and bowed his face to the ground before the king.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Then Araunah said, “Why has my lord the king come to his servant?” And David said, “To buy the threshing floor from you, in order to build an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8714AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8714AB\"></sup>that the plague may be held back from the people.”",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Araunah said to David, “Let my lord the king take and offer up what is good in his sight. Look, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8715AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8715AC\"></sup>the oxen for the burnt offering, the threshing sledges and the yokes of the oxen for the wood.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Everything, O king, Araunah gives to the king.” And Araunah said to the king, “May the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8716AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8716AD\"></sup>accept you.”",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>However, the king said to Araunah, “No, but I will surely buy <i>it</i> from you for a price, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8717AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8717AE\"></sup>I will not offer burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God which cost me nothing.” So <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8717AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8717AF\"></sup>David bought the threshing floor and the oxen for fifty shekels of silver.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>David built there an altar to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NASB-8718AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NASB-8718AG\"></sup>Thus the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was moved by prayer for the land, and the plague was held back from Israel."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;